Commentary.Commentary: Finally!!! We're ready. Usman Khawaja on strike...

The roller is slowly leaving the field now. Australia won't mind the delay. The two umpires get together and they have a worried look on their faces. Perhaps, they are advising Babar Azam to use spinners as the light is not conducive to face fast bowling. Babar consults his deputy, Rizwan, and they have agreed. Shaheen goes off his bowling mark and it's going to be Sajid Khan to start proceedings. More time wasting as the close-in fielders are wearing their protective gears.

The men concerned are back on the field. David Warner and Usman Khawaja are the Aussie openers. Their main aim will be to see off the day's play carefully. That said, they can't get over-defensive against the Pakistan bowlers. Shaheen Afridi is getting ready to bowl the first over. There is a buzz around the stadium. The heavy roller is still doing its job, so there is a small delay. Warner is seen having a word with Shaheen.
... SECOND INNINGS ...

Right then, the crowd is getting excited about the prospect of watching the Pakistan bowlers bowl this evening, that too under lights. They are warming up. Around 56 minutes left in the day's play but considering the fading light, we will be lucky if the play lasts the distance. Anyway, stay tuned as the Australian openers will be out soon with their reply.

Here comes the declaration! Babar Azam whistles and calls his boys back. Pakistan have declared their first innings on 476/4! A strong batting show by the home team after winning the toss. The first three wickets were involved in valuable stands and that propelled them to a sizable total. Imam-ul-Haq and Azhar Ali were the chief architects and the others around them also chipped in with useful runs. Nothing much to write home about Australia's bowling. They toiled hard on a docile surface but without much success. One thing they did do well was to keep the scoring rate under check.
Full and floated around off, Iftikhar Ahmed lunges and eases it to point.
Turning away from the batter, short in length, Ahmed cuts but finds point.
Shortish and on middle, forced down in the gap at mid-wicket for two.
FOUR! A freebie and it has been put away! A low full toss around leg, Iftikhar Ahmed uses his wrists and whips it in the gap at mid-wicket for a boundary.
Short and around off, punched to point.

Floated and full, around middle, spinning away, Iftikhar Ahmed tries to flick but gets a leading edge through covers for a couple. The umpire asks Iftikhar Ahmed to stay away from the danger area while running.
Spears it very full and on middle, Ahmed tries to drive straight but it takes the inner edge and rolls in front of square leg. They cross for a run as Starc chases and slides to collect the ball.
Serves it on a length around middle and off, Iftikhar Ahmed defends it back from the crease.
Fuller and around off, pushed back to the bowler. Rizwan has a word with his partner.
Pitches it up and wide outside off, Rizwan reaches out and drives. The cover fielder misfields and concedes a single.
Short and wide outside off, Ahmed steers it down to deep point for one.
On a good length, angling away from around off, Rizwan decides to leave but is late in withdrawing his bat. It takes the toe end and runs down to third man for a run.

Drinks break. 70 runs in the first segment of play after Tea and there is definitely more intent shown by the Pakistan batters. They lost both Babar Azam and Azhar Ali in the process but have a perfect pair in the middle to do quick scoring. 20 overs left in the day's play, light permitting. It's been overcast for quite some time and we are playing under lights. That might also play a role in Pakistan's declaration as the light is not supposed to improve much. Mitchell Starc to bowl after the break...
Beaten! Excellent drift on this delivery. It lands close to off, spins away a shade as Iftikhar Ahmed prods forward in defense and misses.
Presses forward to a full ball and pushes it through mid off for a single.
Flatter and shorter around middle, Rizwan moves back and forces it to wide long on for a couple.
Tosses it above the eye line and lands it full around off, Iftikhar Ahmed eases it down to long off for one.
A touch flatter and around middle, Rizwan leans and pushes it gently towards cover-point for a brisk single.
Loopy and full, landing around off, Ahmed drives square of the wicket on the off side for a single.
FOUR! Eased away! Short in length and wide outside off, Rizwan plays it late and it goes off the outer half. It's intentional though and the ball races wide of the keeper for a boundary at third man.
Inswinger, around middle, worked down towards mid on.

FOUR! Well played! Josh Hazlewood lands it a touch short and outside off, this one moves away after hitting the surface, Mohammad Rizwan sticks back, opens the face of his bat late and steers it down to deep backward point for a boundary.
Josh is maintaining a great line. Keeps it around off, on a length, Mohammad Rizwan defends it from the back foot.
Once again there is some visible movement into the batter, Rizwan works it away to mid-wicket.
Lands it full and on middle, some reverse in the air, Rizwan brings down a straight bat and defends it to mid on.
Fuller and on off, driven to Smith at covers.
Tossed up, full and around middle, Iftikhar Ahmed opens up in his stance and pushes it more from the outer half to extra cover.
Drags his length short and delivers it on off, Rizwan goes back and punches it with the spin to sweeper cover for one. 450 up!
Too full and around off, this is forced down to long off for a single.
Floated and full, around leg, Ahmed drives it off his front foot to extra cover.
Lovely flight, full and on leg, Rizwan wrists it down to long on for a single.
On off, this is pushed towards cover.
On off, Ahmed strokes it to mid off.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed to mid off for one.
On off, defended.
Good length and on off, this is pushed to covers.
FOUR! Nicely controlled! Lovely shot! Short and on middle, Rizwan pulls it hard through square leg for a boundary.
Loopy one, too full and on off, Iftikhar Ahmed pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and flighted, around off, it's driven off the front foot to covers.
Will Iftikhar Ahmed come ahead of Fawad Alam with Pakistan eyeing quick runs? Yup, here comes Iftikhar at number 6. A slip comes in now.

OUT! TAKEN! Ali misses out on his double ton! Marnus Labuschagne gets a wicket. A good gesture from him, he congratulates Azhar as he walks back. Ali looks to play the reverse sweep, this is tossed up outside off, the ball spins away, there is some extra bounce too. It shoots off the top edge towards short third man. Cameron Green uses his long reach well, as he moves back, stretches his hands out and takes an easy catch. All eyes towards the Pakistan dressing room but there is no sign of a declaration.
Commentary.Howout: c Cameron Green b Marnus Labuschagne

Commentary.Commentary: Outside off, this one turns away. Rizwan looks to drive but it goes off the outside edge towards short third man for one.
On off, Rizwan looks to drive but this turns away and he is beaten.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
On middle, defended.
Drop and run! On off, this is played towards cover for one.
On off, defended.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.

Not a bad appeal but it is going down leg! Rizwan takes a few steps down the track, this is fuller and tails back in from outside off. Rizwan looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. It is going down leg. A leg bye is taken as it rolls on the leg side. Australia opt not to take the DRS, they only have one left.
Shorter and angling into the body, Rizwan looks to pull but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Cummins continues to rotate his bowlers. It's time for yet another spell for Josh Hazlewood (0/38 in 23 overs) who has bowled within himself in this Test match.
Shorter and on middle, this is pulled through mid-wicket for one.
The one now that goes on with the arm, it is defended.

Another lovely ball! This is tossed up nicely, it lands on off and then turns away again. Rizwan lunges and tries to defend but is beaten. Pakistan really won't mind seeing the ball turning the way it is now.
BEATEN! That is a beauty! This lands on off and then spins away. Rizwan looks to defend but is beaten.
Half an appeal! This lands on middle, turns away a touch. Rizwan looks to play the paddle scoop but is hit on the body. Turned down.
On off, Ali pushes it through covers and takes one.
Marnus Labuschagne returns to bowl. 0 for 33 in his 7 overs so far.
Fuller and on off, Rizwan strokes it to covers.
Back of a length and on off, Rizwan hangs back and defends.
Slightly shorter and on off, Rizwan guides it to point again.
Off the inner half! Fuller and on middle, this tails back in. Ali looks to drive, it goes off the inner half down to fine leg for one.
Outside off, Rizwan waits and then guides it through point for one.
Fuller and on middle, Rizwan flicks but to mid-wicket.

SIX! High and handsome! A loopy off spinner, landing full around middle, Azhar Ali goes down, hits it with the turns and smokes it over mid-wicket. Usman Khawaja thinks that he is in with a chance but it sails over his head.
Flatter and full on middle, drilled down to long on for another run.
Flighted and on off, bunted to mid off for a quick run.
Width there outside off, Rizwan goes back and forces it to extra cover for a single.
Tossed up and wide outside off, it's eased through covers for a single.
Full and on off, Ali flicks it with the spin to mid-wicket.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
The length is short again, Azhar strokes it to sweeper cover and takes a single. He wants another run but Rizwan has slipped.
Rizwan now takes one as he strokes it to mid off.
Fuller and on off, this is hit towards mid off for one more.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
A cracking yorker to begin a new spell from Green. It's around middle and Ali does well to dig it out.

Appeal for a run out! It's referred upstairs... Full and floated outside off, Ali drives it firmly to extra cover where Cummins makes a tumbling stop. Azhar charges to the other end for a single Rizwan is ball-watching but then races to the other end. Pat throws it to the bowler who takes the bails off but Azhar is found safe in the replays.
Rizwan opens his account. Full and around off, Mohammad Rizwan gets forward and knocks it down to long on for one.
Flatter and shorter on middle, defended back.
DROPPED! Short and wide outside off, Mohammad Rizwan goes for a full-blooded square cut but gets a thick outside edge behind. Alex Carey fails to hold on to the catch and Rizwan gets a reprieve.

Aerial but safe! Lyon senses the charge from the batter and drops it a bit short, around off, Ali is down the track for a big hit but only manages to drag it off the bottom half. It doesn't carry to long on and they cross for a single.
Fuller in length, around leg, it's swept well but straight to short fine leg.
On the stumps, defended.
On off, this is pushed towards cover. A run taken.
Outside off, left alone.
Leg bye! On the pads, Azhar looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls behind towards fine leg. Two taken.
Good length and on the stumps, Ali keeps it out easily.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Quicker and on middle, Rizwan plays it to mid-wicket.
Flatter and on middle, blocked.
Tossed up and on off, defended.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Floats it up on off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Mohammad Rizwan is the next batter.

OUT! RUN OUT! BABAR IS WELL SHORT! Another big stand comes to an end. A run out is probably the only way one of these two could have been dismissed. Excellent from Marnus Labuschagne and such efforts can surely lift the side. This is on middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket. Azam calls for one. Marnus Labuschagne there runs to his right, picks the ball up, turns his body and has a shy at the bowler's end. He hits, the umpire takes it upstairs but Australia are celebrating. Replays roll in and they show Azam is easily short. He is gutted as he walks back.

Direct hit! Marnus Labuschagne has knocked the stumps down with a direct hit at the non-striker's end. Australia are celebrating. The umpire nods his head and then takes it upstairs. The replays confirm the departure of Babar Azam.
On the stumps, Ali gets right behind the line and defends.
Fuller and on middle, Ali pushes it to mid on.
Another one on the stumps, Ali stands tall and plays it onto the ground.
Back of a length and on off, Ali pushes it to covers.
On middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
The 100-run stand is up and it comes in quick time! Exactly the kind of partnership Pakistan needed. This is on off, it is pushed to mid off for a quick run.
On off, Azam plays it to covers.
Loopy ball on off, Azam is happy to play a defensive stroke.
Another one tossed up nicely. Azam leans forward and keeps it out.
Floats it up on middle, Babar walks forward and then defends.
On middle, this is worked to square leg.
Ali steps down the track, he hits it hard through covers for one.
Fuller and on middle, Azam flicks but to mid-wicket.
A little too straight, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Good length and on off, Azam defends it onto the ground.
Misfield and a run is taken! On off, Ali hits it on the up towards cover. The fielder lets it through and a run is taken.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Good length and on middle, this one holds its line. Ali is squared up as he tries to block. Does well to get his bat on the ball.
As expected, there is a bowling change. Pat Cummins brings himself into the attack. 1/58 in his 25 overs so far.
Now onto 97 as this is pushed down to long on for one.
Another single! On middle, this is eased down to long on for one. Runs have come nicely for this pair. The stand is already 96.
On middle, Azam flicks it to mid-wicket.
On middle, this is eased down to long on for one.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket. Marnus Labuschagne runs in and as he tries to pick the ball up, he slips, falls awkwardly, but no harm is done.
On off, this is pushed through covers for one.

FOUR! This is deft again! This is very deft! Wonderful. 12 from the first over after the break! This is outside off, slower. Ali, waits, waits and waits and just before it goes into the gloves of the keeper, he guides it fine and into the third man fence. David Warner chases but in vain.
Ali shapes up for the paddle scoop, this is bowled outside off and turning away further. He leaves eventually.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries and the 400 is up! Deft touch! Outside off, shorter and turning away with extra bounce. Ali guides it past first slip and into the fence.

FOUR! That has been hit hard! The sweep is out, it is on middle, Ali smashes it through square leg and bags a boundary. Probably we are now in for some fun. Both the batters will activate their T20 mode.
Tossed up on middle, defended.
The umpire gets one of the bails changed as it was not lighting up properly.
Tossed up on off, this is pushed to covers.
All in readiness again in Rawalpindi. The players are taking the field. It has turned a shade overcast at the moment. Marnus Labuschagne is going to continue with his spell from this end...
... DAY 2, SESSION 3 ...

Another session where Pakistan had a bigger say than Australia! The tourists did manage to end the drought by claiming the wicket of Imam-ul-Haq but it was like an oasis in the desert. The arrival of Babar Azam injected some much-needed momentum as the run rate of his stand with Azhar Ali hovered around 4. 92 runs came in the afternoon session and Pakistan are marching towards a massive total in the first innings. For how long will they bat? Are they thinking about declaration this evening? 38 overs left in the day's play and the way things stand, Australia could be in for a leather hunt in the final session. Do join us at 3.30 pm IST (10 am GMT).
The last ball of the session is negotiated! On middle, defended. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2!
A single! On middle, this is pushed to the right of the bowler who dives over the ball and a run is taken.
On the stumps, Ali once again plays it to mid-wicket.
On middle, this is flicked through mid-wicket for one more.
On middle, Azam plays it back to the bowler.
Floats it up on middle, Azam keeps it out.
Around off, shorter, Ali guides it to point.
Flatter and on middle, defended.
A single, this time he finds the gap in the cover region with the drive.
On off, this is pushed to covers.

150 for Azhar Ali! He continues to pile on the misery on the visitors. Gets there by easing this full ball down to long off for one. Ali has a big smile on his face, he just loves to score against Australia, has a double century in Australia as well.
Outside off, the leg spinner, it is played to covers.
On the pads, Azam once again finds the square leg fielder after working it on the leg side.
On the pads, Azam works it to square leg.
Another single as this is clipped through mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed down to wide long off for one.
Floats it up on off, Azam keeps it out.
On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
A single to end as this is pushed through covers.
Another one on off, kept out.
Tossed up on off, this is pushed to covers.
Bowls this one slightly short and outside off, it is cut through point for one.
Another one tossed up nicely and on off, blocked. Marnus Labuschagne has started well.
Lands it well, to begin with! This is tossed up on off, a little bit of turn. Azam looks to defend, it goes off the outer half to point.
Marnus Labuschagne to have a go with Tea approaching. He has bowled 4 overs so far in this match.
Two runs to finish and Ali moves 4 short of 150! On middle, this is whipped through mid-wicket.
Flatter and on middle, Ali defends.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed down to long off for one.
On off, turning back in. Azam nudges it to mid-wicket.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed towards cover.
Floats it up on off, Ali pushes it towards cover for one.
A dot to end! Good length and on off, Azam blocks.
Angled into middle, Ali nudges it through square leg for one more.
FOUR! Just helps it on its way! Nice and fine! Short and on the body, this is pulled fine on the leg side. It races away to the fence.
Good length and on off, Ali defends.
Not timed that well and Azam is not happy with himself! Fuller and on off, Azam drives it but more off the toe end towards mid off for one.
Angled into the pads, Ali works it through square leg for one.
A dot to end! On the pads, this is worked to square leg.
Sent back in time! On off, this is pushed towards the left of the bowler. Ali wants one, he takes off but Azam sends him back in time.
Floated up on off, blocked.
The reverse sweep comes out, it is played towards deep point for one.
Tossed up on off, defended.
That has spun big! This lands around off and spins down the leg side. Ali looks to flick but misses.

Fuller and on off, angling in, Babar clips it towards short mid-wicket where the fielder dives and makes a partial stop. It's deflected towards mid on, Babar steps out looking for a run but is sent back.
Delivers it on a length around off, Babar defends it by covering the line and movement.
On a length and outside off, Babar stays back and taps it down to backward point.
Fullish and on off, Babar defends it back to the bowler and Hazlewood attempts for a clever back-flick. He doesn't release the ball though and just looks behind.
Movement in the air. Full and swinging in around middle, Babar pushes it down to mid on.
Good length, around off and curling back in, Babar defends late near his body.
Flighted and full, outside off, again Azhar uses his feet and opens the face of his bat in time. Finds the gap through wide mid off and takes two.
Jumps down the track to a full ball but only manages to push it back to the bowler.
Flighted and on off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
A bit short and on off, Babar goes back and strokes it to long on for a run.

Good work from Steven Smith, great anticipation. Full and around off, Azhar brings out the reverse sweep and Smith immediately moves across to his right from slip. He makes a half-stop and they take a single.
Fuller and on off, Azhar plays ahead of his front pad and pushes it to mid-wicket.
Fuller in length, around leg, shaping down, Babar fails to flick and Alex Carey dives across to his left to collect the ball.
Almost drags it on! Hazlewood serves it close to off, it lands and nips in off the seam, Ali tries to defend but gets an inside edge through his legs. It goes to square leg and they cross.
On a good length, around off, Azhar sticks on the back foot and works it with the angle to mid-wicket.
Josh keeps it around off, on a length, Ali is watchfully behind the line in defense.
This one goes more with the angle of the bowler, on a good length, Ali keeps it out to mid-wicket.
Some visible late movement there as it lands on a length around off, Azhar defends close to his front pad.
Josh Hazlewood (20-5-30-0) is back into the attack. Cummins is rotating his pacers here in hope of some success.
Very solid! Tosses it up on off again. Azam prods forward and keeps it out.
On off, this is defended.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Another one tossed up outside off, Azam looks to defend, it goes off the outer half towards point for one.

FOUR! Lovely shot! The sweep comes out, it is on middle, Azam hits it hard through square leg. This one races away to the fence. Azam has scored quite freely. Just the kind of innings Pakistan needed. The 50-run stand comes up.
Tossed up on off, Azam lunges and blocks.
Hurls it across very full and on off, Azhar forces it back past the bowler. Cummins runs across to his right from mid off and makes a sliding stop.
Angling in from a length around off, Azhar closes the face of his bat and defends it to short mid-wicket.
Starc is bowling from 'round the wicket to Babar as well. His line though is all over the place. Full and on the pads, Azam clips it in acres of space at deep mid-wicket for three runs.
Lands it on a length and around off, shaping in, Azhar tries to defend but it takes the inner edge. The ball rolls behind square leg and they cross.
FOUR! That's a beautiful shot! Azhar Ali has driven well in this knock. Slightly overpitched outside off, at 138.3 kph, Ali transfers his weight on the front foot and crunches it through covers.
Starc speeds in from 'round the wicket and sprays a length ball down the leg side, Ali shuffles across the stumps to flick but misses.
Tossed up around off, turning in a shade, Babar goes back and dead-bats it on the surface.
Full and floated on middle, defended back.
Lyon pulls his length back and delivers it around off, Ali goes back and nudges it through mid-wicket.
SIX! Dismissed! This is not the first time Azhar has charged Lyon. Dances down the track to a full ball and powers it with the spin over wide long on. Meaty blow from Ali!
Goes on the back foot to a short ball and punches it towards long on for a run.
Flighted and full outside off, Babar pushes it to covers.
Nathan Lyon is back into the attack. 1 for 114 in his 40 overs thus far.
Starc is again 'round the wicket to Azhar. He goes wide of the crease and spears in a full ball around off, Ali tries to defend and does so from the inner half of his blade.
Back of a length, on the hips of Babar, he easily glances it behind square leg for one.
Starc returns to over the wicket for Babar and slants across a shortish ball outside off, the Pakistan skipper offers no shot.
Short and wide outside off, it's calmly guided down to third man for a run.

FOUR! The outfield has gone quicker and quicker after all the rain on Thursday. Starc switches to 'round the wicket and darts a full ball on middle and leg, Azhar clips it with good timing and finds the gap at mid-wicket. Cameron Green gives the chase, puts in a dive near the fence but fails to pull it back in.
Slightly short and around off, Babar gets back and gently helps it towards square leg for a single.

Drinks break. The last hour was a good one for Australia where they, at last, found the breakthrough. The going from Pakistan continued to be slow but the runs have started to come at a better rate since the arrival of Babar Azam. They surely will be looking to add a lot more in the next hour. Mitchell Starc to continue after the break...
Three more! Lovely timing again! This is fuller and it tails back in from off. Azam pushes it past mid off and takes three.
Another one outside off, not played at.
That swung late! Fuller and outside off, left alone.
On off, defended.
A bumper now, Green did not like getting hit to the fence. Azam evades it well.

FOUR! Delightful! Azam at his full flow is so pleasing to the eye! Another glorious shot from him! Fuller and on off, Azam shows the full face of the bat and strokes it past mid off. It races away to the fence.

FOUR! That is beautifully played! Length and outside off, Ali leans into it and strokes it through covers. Just beautiful. Did not try to overhit it, only used the pace of the bowler and found the gap.
Outside off, Ali leaves it alone.
Length and on off, Ali pushes it to mid off.
Slips this one down the leg side, Ali looks to flick but misses.
On middle, Ali works it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Mitchell Starc returns. 20-5-48-0 are his figures so far.
Two to end! Shorter and outside off, this is hit through covers for two.
Good length and on off, Azam blocks.
Gets really good shape yet again, begins this from closer to the off pole but not close enough to make the batter play.
Another one on a length and outside off, Azam watches it go to the keeper.
Takes this one away, the line is outside off though. Left alone.
Goes fuller and gets it to tail back in. Ali works it to mid-wicket and takes one. He is not planting that front foot way too across for now.
Serves it full and outside off at 140 clicks, Babar gets forward and drives but finds the mid off fielder.
A touch short in length, this time the angle of the bowler takes it around leg, Azhar glances it to deep square leg for one.
Around off, approaching the batsman with the angle, Azhar uses his wrists and keeps it out safely to short mid-wicket.
Fuller in length and outside off, Babar drives it to the left of mid off. Starc slides to stop and they cross for a single.
Angles in a length ball around off, at 138.5 kph, Babar is on the back foot as he defends it to the off side.
Width there outside off, Azhar opens the face of his bat and glides it down to third man for a single.
A harmless nut to end, outside off, left alone.
On off, Azam plays it out on the off side.
Yet another one on a length and outside off, Azam leaves it alone.
Outside off, Azam shoulders arms to this one.
On off, Azam pushes it to covers.
Well bowled! This starts outside off and then comes back in. Azam looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Green is getting the ball to move both ways.
A dot to end! On off, Ali keeps it out.
Two! Really good running! Length and on off, Ali dabs it late and down towards third man. He takes two.
Shorter and down the leg side, Ali looks to pull but misses.
Shorter and on the body, this is tucked through square leg for one.
Outside off, Ali guides it down to third man for one.
Good length and on off, defended.

FOUR! Straight down the ground! What a shot that is to get off the mark! Delightful! Fuller and on off, this one shapes back in. Azam shows the full face and creams it down the ground for a boundary. There was no followthrough to it, just a push. Beautiful stuff.
Nice late movement! He got the ball to move away last time and this time brings it back in from outside off. Azam looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, Azam shoulders arms to this one.
On the fuller side, a little bit of shape away. It is played back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, Ali waits and then guides it down to third man for one.
Good length and on middle, Azam lunges and blocks. End of a successful over for Cummins.
Babar Azam is the new batter at number 4 after the double century stand.

OUT! THE FINGER IS RAISED! Pat Cummins has got Imam LBW or has he? Imam reviews and IT IS TAKEN UPSTAIRS! THREE REDS AND IMAM WALKS BACK! He also takes a review along and Australia have finally broken the marathon stand and ended the marathon innings from the opener. It is the skipper who delivers for Australia. He goes fuller this time, it starts around middle and leg and tails back in late. Imam plants his front foot across but then fails to get his bat down in time. It hits his pad as the flick shot is missed. An appeal and up goes the finger. Imam reviews but in vain.
Angled into the pads, Ali flicks it through square leg and takes one.
Good length and on off, defended.

SHOUT FOR A CATCH! Not given and Australia take the DRS. That was nowhere near the glove and Australia lose another review! Really not sure why they went for that. Not a lot of people appealed. It was more in desperation. A short one down the leg side. Ali looks to pull but misses. There is a couple of Australian fielders who appeal but it is turned down. Australia review to our surprise. UltraEdge gives a negative result.
Angled into middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Another one nicely flighted and on off, Imam is happy to defend.
Well Imam probably has no such intentions. This is floated up on off, it is blocked.
The sweep is out, it is hit through square leg for one. Maybe this shot is signs of Pakistan getting a lot more aggressive now.
On middle, defended.

FOUR! Just over! 100 up for Azhar Ali. He would have surely had his heart in his mouth for a second but he can now celebrate. His 19th ton in Test and he just loves playing against Australia. Has a really good record against them and it is another innings to remember. A very patient knock. He though took the aggressive route to get to his ton. Steps out and despite there being a deep mid on, he goes for the hit. Does not get it right off the middle but hits it well enough to beat that fielder.
Tossed up on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Another short one, this does not get up a lot. Imam lets it go over him.
Another one on a length and around off, this is pushed to covers.
Good length and on off, Imam pushes it to covers.
A bumper now, change in length. Saw that a lot from Cummins in the first session but not too many so far in the short span now. Imam ducks under it.
Attacks the stumps, makes the batter play again. Imam shows the maker's name and plays it to mid on.
Angled into middle, this is played to mid-wicket.
On middle, defended. Australia continue to keep it tight.
Flatter this time and on middle, Ali hangs back and blocks.
Good cricket all around! This is nicely bowled. Lyon tosses it above the eye line and lands it on off. Imam plays it with soft hands on the off side and takes a quick run.
Loopy delivery on off, this is worked down to long on for one.
Slightly shorter in length and on middle, Ali nudges it on the leg side.
Flatter and on middle, Ali pushes it to mid-wicket.
Well played in the end! This one tails back in a long way from off. It is fuller. Imam does well to get his front pad out of the way and works it to mid-wicket.
Just around off, Imam waits and then plays it to gully.
On a length and around off, defended.

The 200-run stand is up! This partnership has surely drained the Aussies, both mentally and physically. They have gone along at their own pace and have taken Pakistan to a position where losing the game for them seems unlikely. They will though now want to up the ante a touch. Ali works this ball on the pads to fine leg and takes one.
Angled on middle, Ali works it to mid-wicket.
Pat Cummins to bowl.
Shorter and on middle, Imam pulls it through mid-wicket for one.
On off, Ali pushes it to covers. So just the single in the first over after the break.
This time lands it on off, Ali defends it onto the ground.

A little too straight again, this is nudged to backward square leg. Now with not a lot of turn on offer, Lyon is bowling a lot more on the stumps, he usually bowls it nicely outside and gets it to turn back in but has to stick to bowling at the stumps here.
Tossed up on middle, Ali leans forward and plays it to mid-wicket again.
Flatter and on middle, Ali hangs back and works it to mid-wicket.
A run on the first ball of the session! Imam steps out, gets to the pitch of it and eases it down to long off for one.

Welcome back, folks! The men concerned are back on the field. The ball was reversing before the break and expect Australia to come out attacking and pick a few wickets. Also, Pakistan would look to change their strategy and score more quickly than the first session. Nathan Lyon to start proceedings...
... DAY 2, SESSION 2 ...

There was one notable moment in the morning session. It was off the bowling of Nathan Lyon. Imam-ul-Haq had tried to cut the ball but without any success. Alex Carey put in a very muted appeal for a caught behind and the bowler also didn't press much. Later on, the UltraEdge showed a spike and a golden chance to get a breakthrough went begging. Anyway, in the end stages of the session, the pair of Josh Hazlewood and Mitchell Starc caused some issues. Starc was seen hiding the ball in his bowling run-up which indicates that Australia believe that the ball is reversing and they will bank on it to bring them some luck after the break. Do join us at 1.10 pm IST (7:40 am GMT) for the post-Lunch session.

Azhar Ali (95*) smiles and admits that there are butterflies in his tummy but he will try to stay calm as he has done it many times in the past. Tells that the Aussie bowlers tried very hard and later on, there was some reverse swing happening too. Shares that they wanted to absorb the pressure in the morning and will now look to build on this. Further says that they will discuss their approach from hereon in this break.

A session in slow-mo! Just 57 runs scored by Pakistan and you have to give credit to Australia for maintaining a firm lid on the scoring rate as the wickets refused to come. The Aussies bowled with a lot of disciplined and accuracy, and for a change, there was some spice from the surface. A few deliveries bounced more than expected, catching the batters off-guard but Azhar Ali and Imam-ul-Haq countered them quite judiciously. The latter has notched up a 150-plus score while the latter is 5 short of his century. It's going to be a nervous break for Azhar! Here he is, giving a quick flash interview...
A single then to end the session! Fuller and on off, Imam pushes it to mid off for one. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Starc goes short! A surprise short ball, Ali easily pulls it down to fine leg and gets to the other end.
Shorter and on off, Ali stays back and pushes it to covers.
Length again and on off, Ali keeps it out.
On the off pole, Ali pushes it to covers.
Angling away from the off pole. Ali covers his off pole and lets it go.
Josh goes very full on this occasion, around off, Imam plays a punch on drive, finds mid on.
Full and landing around off, tailing back in a shade, Imam gets forward and defends it from the inside part of his blade.
Slightly short and on top of off, at 133.3 kph, Imam-ul-Haq goes on his toes and defends it to covers.
On a length and close to off, Imam goes on the back foot and jams it down towards mid on.
Pitches it up and around off, Imam is on the front foot in defense.
Four leg byes! Josh Hazlewood gets his line wrong, serves it down the leg side, Imam fails to flick but it takes his thigh pad and scoots past the diving keeper for a boundary at fine leg. 300 up!
End of a good over by Starc! Another one on a length and on off, kept out.
And again, Starc lands it on a length and pitches it around off. Ali plays it late and onto the ground.

That is a beauty! Starc has looked dangerous in this spell. He has got the ball to move and is causing problems. This is slightly fuller and it tails away from the off pole. Azhar looks to push at it but is beaten. It was more of a tentative push.
That is a really good short one, on middle, Ali moves out of the way.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length and on off, defended.
Josh now gets some swing, he tails it back in from off. It is worked to mid on for one.
Drop and run! On off, Imam plays it on the off side for one.
Back of a length and on middle, defended.
Good length and on middle, making the batter play. Defended.
Fuller and on middle, that is probably the line Josh will bowl quite a lot with the field he has set. It is pushed to mid on.
On middle, Imam works it to mid-wicket. Two fielders there waiting for one hit up in the air.
Josh Hazlewood is back for another spell before Lunch. 0/28 in his 18 overs so far.
Late movement! Ali played that well in the end. Fuller and it starts on off, moves away late. Ali watches it and lets it go.
On off, length, it is pushed to covers.
That is a beauty! This starts on middle and keeps moving away. It is a length ball. Ali is beaten as he tries to block. First real signs of reverse swing.
Some nice shape away! Fuller and outside off, gets it to move away. Left alone.
Angled into the pads, Imam flicks it through mid-wicket for one more.
Imam indicates that has stayed low! On middle, length. Imam blocks it.

Three more and that is 150 for Imam! A really solid knock so far but it is probably time for him to up the ante a little. He gets another short ball on middle, he stays back and works it through mid-wicket. Not timed as good as the last one but three taken.

FOUR! This is adding salt to the wound. Could have had Imam a few balls ago but instead is hit for a boundary by him! This is way too short, probably worried about Imam coming down the track, Imam goes back and whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On middle, blocked.
On off, Ali strokes it through covers for one.
On off, this is pushed down to long off for one.

An appeal for a caught behind but without much conviction! There was a sound but it was not woody! Shorter and outside off, Imam looks to cut but is beaten. There is an appeal but nothing from the umpire. Now then, UltraEdge shows a spike as the ball passes the bottom of the bat. An opportunity goes by. Australia just seem flat at the moment, quite understandably but there was a sound there and the appeal could have been with more enthusiasm.
Another single! Outside off, Imam plays it through point and takes one.
Shorter and outside off, Ali opens the face of the bat and guides it down to third man for one.
This time goes full, gives the ball time to do its bit, it though goes on with the angle, on off, Ali pushes it to mid off.

Attacks the stumps yet again, makes the batter play, Ali negotiates it well. It will be interesting to see if Starc gets some reverse swing. Nothing for now but he has been quite shorter than one would like.
Another one on the stumps, Azhar Ali manages to keep it out again.
Good length and on middle, defended.
Mitchell Starc to have his first burst this morning. 0/43 in his 16 overs so far.
Flatter and outside off, Imam shoulders arms to it.

Off the leading edge but once again, it is in the gap and a run is taken. On the pads, Ali looks to flick, he is a touch early in closing the face of the bat. It goes off the leading edge towards mid on for one.
On middle, defended.

FOUR! A reverse sweep from Ali! That comes as a surprise. He has played it brilliantly though and moves into the 90s! On middle, Ali gets on top of the bounce, rolls his wrists and hits it behind point, all along the ground for a boundary.

A little bit of confusion but safe! However, there was a single there. On the pads, this is flicked towards mid-wicket. Ali wants one, he is halfway down the wicket but is sent back and Pat Cummins makes a sliding stop.
Flatter and on middle, Ali works it to mid-wicket.
A harmless delivery to end. Outside off, left alone.
On the bounce! They have a fielder placed for that shot, hoping that Imam hits it in the air. Shortish and outside off, Imam cuts but into the ground and on the bounce to a catching point fielder.
Back of a length and on off, Imam guides it to point.
Wide outside off, Imam has no interest in playing at it.
Two is the call and two is what they get! This is full and outside off, Imam opens the face of the bat and squeezes it past point.
Outside off, angling away further. Left alone.

Are Australia not happy with the ball? David Warner, Pat Cummins, Steven Smith and Marnus Labuschagne are seen having a look at the nut. It's looking quite roughed up. Oh, they are trying to find the shinier side. Ball management is the key in these conditions.
Another run to end! Imam uses his feet again, he then eases it down to long on for one.
On middle, Ali works it down to long on and gets to the other end.
On middle, Ali defends.
Tosses it up nicely and on middle, Ali defends.
On the pads, this is flicked but to short leg.
Some aggression from Imam! Steps out and gets close to the pitch of the ball, it is pushed down to long off for one.
Yet another dot so that is 17 dots after that boundary! On the middle pole, Ali keeps it out.
Pakistan are in no hurry at the moment! Yet again a defensive stroke to this ball on middle. No urgency shown by them so far in the morning session, they are happy to not force things.
Solid! Angled into middle, Ali shows the full face of the bat and plays it to mid off.
On middle, from wide of the crease. Ali plays it to mid-wicket.

Misses out! Green was probably looking for a yorker but ends up serving a full toss, Ali is taken by surprise a little. He ends up flicking it but too close to square leg who stops it with a dive to his right.
On middle, Ali pushes it to mid on.
Slightly shorter, Imam hangs back and clips it to mid-wicket. So, 11 dots after that boundary.
A little bit quicker this time, attacks the stumps though. Imam is solid in defense.
This time gives it nice air and lands it around off, defended.
Now probably because of the last delivery, Lyon pushes this one through, the length is shorter, Imam stays back and works it to square leg.
Imam uses his feet and works it nicely to mid-wicket.
Nicely tossed up and it lands on middle, Imam defends.

Drinks break. Another hour of hard work for the Aussies. The only thing they have done well is to not allow Pakistan free runs. 27 runs this morning in the 13 overs so far. The pitch has certainly spiced up a little and there is some visible extra bounce. So far, Azhar and Imam have countered it well though. What's in store in the next hour?
Back of a length, on middle, Azhar stands tall inside the crease and plays it down to square leg.
Pitches it up and around middle, Ali brings down a straight bat and pushes it down to mid on.
Gets away there! Cameron Green again delivers a full ball down the leg side, this time Ali has failed to flick it off his pads.
Bouncer around off, to push the batter back, Azhar goes on the back foot and sways away.
Better line, around off, on a fuller line, Ali defends it to the off side.
FOUR! Eased away! Wrong line from Green, dishes it on a length and down the leg side, Azhar nudges it fine and it races away to the fence, beating Josh Hazlewood's dive near the boundary line.
Floats it up on off, Imam comes forward and plays it onto the ground.
On the stumps, Imam is solid in defense.
On the stumps, Imam plays it back to the bowler.
Flatter and on middle, kept out.
Imam comes down the track, he ends up yorking himself, it is jammed back to the bowler.
On the pads, this is flicked through mid-wicket for one.
On middle, defended.
Uppish but wide! On middle, this is flicked, in the air but wide of mid-wicket for one.
Length and on off again, Imam this time opens the face of the bat and guides it through point for one.
On off, Imam pushes it to covers.
Length and outside off from around the wicket, left alone.
Shorter and angled into the pads, Ali works it down to fine leg and gets to the other end.
Still, no signs of Mitchell Starc. Cameron Green comes into the attack. Just 5 overs from him in this match. Australia seem to be managing his workload a little too much.

A single to end! Not the best of overs from Lyon. He was a tad too short and a little too quicker than one should be bowling here. On the pads, Ali clips it through mid-wicket, this time finds the gap and takes one.
And again, a lot flatter and shorter than Lyon would have liked. Azhar waits and then flicks it to mid-wicket.
Pushes it through and on middle, Ali hangs back and defends.
A little bit of turn for Lyon! Slightly flatter on middle, this one spins back in. Ali stays back and works it on the leg side.
Azhar Ali comes down the track now, the length though is slightly shorter from Lyon. Ali adjusts and defends.
Tossed up on off, Ali pushes it to covers.
Nathan Lyon is into the attack for the first time this morning. 31-4-87-1 are his figures so far. A slip, leg slip, short leg in place.
This one goes through at a good click. On middle, short again. Imam again evades it. He has a look at the surface after that, probably surprised by the pace.

That just did not come off as quickly as it has been doing off the surface! Short and on middle, this does not bounce a lot and comes a lot slower off the surface. Imam does well to move out of the way. He initially just ducked but since there was a lack of bounce, he also had to move his head out of the way.
Bangs it short this time and on the body, this is a slower one. Ali waits and then with soft hands, tucks it towards square leg and gets to the other end.
This time it is quicker, this short one is a lot quicker than the last ball. Ali lets it go.

FOUR! You will have to convince us that Azhar Ali intended to play that shot. Still, you won't succeed. It was just a late thought from him. Short and around off, Azhar crouches and almost looks like he wants to withdraw his bat. But he is late and then the shot appears to be an intentional one, flying over gully. A ramp shot from Azhar Ali, that in itself is unbelievable. Anyway, it's a boundary.
Good length and on off, Ali defends.
Dot to end! Outside off, left alone. Just the one from the over.
And again, he gets some movement into the batter, the line is a little too straight and it is clipped towards fine leg for one.
Too high! Some movement for Josh! It lands outside off and jags back in. Ali looks to put his bat on the ball but misses to get hit near the box. A muted appeal for an lbw dies down instantly.
Slightly shorter in length and on off, Ali arches and lets it go to the keeper.
Another one on a length and on off, blocked.
Just outside off, good disciplined line. Left alone.
Good stuff from the Aussies! Keeping it tight and not letting Pakistan off the hook. Length and on middle, Imam plays it onto the ground. Does well there to negotiate with the extra bounce.
Angled into the middle pole, this is worked to square leg.
Another short one, that is three in a row. Imam has no interest in playing at it again. That unconvincing pull shot is perhaps still playing in his mind.
That one has flown through! Short again. Imam ducks under it. Carey collects it above his head.
This time Imam takes the challenge of pulling this short ball, he does not time it all that well but gets it away from deep square leg for two.
Back of a length and on off, this is pushed to mid off.
A maiden by Hazlewood. On middle, this is pushed to mid off.
Length and on middle, Ali shows the full face of the bat and pushes it back to the bowler.
Back of a length and on middle, Azhar pushes it back to the bowler.
Angled into middle, Ali works it to mid-wicket.
Yet another bumper, this is on the body, Azhar lets it go over him. Australia do have a plan to bowl short at the batters today but on this wicket, it is being negotiated quite well.
Just outside off, Azhar leaves it alone.
A bumper to end then! On middle, Imam lets it go over him.
Slightly fuller and on middle, Imam pushes it down to mid on for one.
Another one which takes off after landing just ahead of a shorter length. Ali nudges it down to fine leg and takes one.
The physio comes out! That snorter from Pat Cummins perhaps brushed the grille of his helmet as well. A mandatory concussion check is going on. Imam is fine.

That has gotten big on the batter! That is a nasty delivery. First signs of the wicket misbehaving. This is on a back of a length, rising quite a lot after landing. Imam is taken by surprise. He looks to fend it away but it hits the shoulder of the bat, then the helmet and it rolls towards point. Well played in the end. The batters cross. Soft hands are the key to such deliveries.
Another one on the stumps, it is kept out.
On off, Imam pushes it to covers.
A harmless nut to end, it's outside off and left alone. There has been no movement for the pacers today. The ball is still relatively new but it has done nothing in the air and off the surface.
Another short one, Ali lets it go to the keeper.
On the off pole, Ali plays it to mid off.
Another couple! Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg. Two taken.
Good length again and on off, Ali is solid in defense once more.
Just outside off, in the 5th stump channel. Ali makes a good leave by covering the off pole.
On the stumps, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length and on off, Imam-ul-Haq stays back and defends.
Two more! Outside off, Imam-ul-Haq drives it through covers for two.
Uppish but in the gap! Three in the end! On middle, Ali works it in the air but wide of mid-wicket for three.
That one takes off too! Length and on middle, Azhar once again looks to block but this hits the splice.
Another one on the stumps, blocked.
On middle, defended.
Imam probably misses out! However, they have a field set for that shot. This is on the pads, full, Imam flicks, there is a mid-wicket and a square leg. The latter dives and stops it.
Good length, this one zips through. Imam defends. The pitch seems to have quickened up a touch.
First run of the day! This is angled into the pads, Ali nudges it around the corner and gets to the other end.
Right on the money to begin with by him too! Length and on off, Ali stays back and blocks.
Who will bowl from the other end? Josh Hazlewood (14-3-24-0) it is.
A maiden to begin with! End of an aggressive over by Cummins. The 4th short ball of the over. Imam spots it early and ducks under it.
On the fuller side, Imam-ul-Haq leans into it and strokes it back towards the bowler.
Really good start from Cummins, no looseners from him to begin with. This is now fuller than the last three balls, length and on middle, defended.

That is really well bowled! Bending his back here is Cummins. Short again and this one gets big on the batter. Imam does well to take one hand off the handle while defending, it goes off the splice to the off side.
Follows a bumper with another one banged in short and on middle, Imam sways away from this one too.
Starts off with a bumper, probably looking to catch the batter by surprise. Imam though spots it well and he ducks under it.

We are moments away from the first ball of the day! The Australian players walk out wearing black arm bands. They are then followed by the Pakistan players and there is going to be a moment of silence for the legend, Shane Warne. Now the Aussies walk out to the middle and so do Imam-ul-Haq and Azhar Ali who will continue their innings. Pat Cummins will begin. Here we go...

As cliche as it may sound, the show must go on! The best way to celebrate a legend is by playing the game he adored. It won't be easy for the Aussie players but they will have to overcome the emotions and perform. Currently, as per the match situation, they have their backs to the wall. The surface hasn't assisted them and Pakistan are racing away with the game. The second new ball still has the shine and hardness intact, can they make use of it in the morning conditions? We will find out soon.

Remembering the great. For every 90s kid, Shane Warne won't be just a bowler, he was the style icon, the ultimate crowd puller, a cricket mind like no one. Everyone remembers the enormous success he achieved in Test cricket but very few remember that it all started with figures of 1 for 150. The journey after that for the leggie was awe-inspiring which is a testament to his class and character. He made leg-spin bowling a fashion. A 'cool' art. Whoever aspired to be a leggie, the action of Shane came naturally to him. His 'Ball of the Century' is etched in cricketing folklore. A young boy took the biggest rivalry in cricket, The Ashes, by storm with his first delivery. The world of cricket was never the same, Warne changed the dynamics and showed that wrist spinners from outside the subcontinent can also rule the roost. Thank you for the memories, Warnster!

His bowling was poetry in motion! His control over the ball was impeccable! His variations were too hot to handle! His leg spinners turned a mile! His googlies foxed the best in the business. His flippers whipped the minds of many! His top spinners toppled many greats! His sliders breached many defense! Add to it - Gilly, Haydo, Punter consistently chirping from behind along with the ever-expressive Aussie crowd, what an era that was! Truly a wizard, Shane Keith Warne. Leg spin bowling is a complex art and he was the Ultimate Master. 'Bowling Shane' will reverberate in our ears forever.

Shane Warne is no more! The cricket world is in shock! It's absolutely tragic. Within a few hours, we've lost two stalwarts in Rodney Marsh and the spin wizard. Everyone is mourning and social media is flooded with messages. The past and current cricketers, the fans across the globe, are remembering the magician with the ball. Warney will be missed badly. Gone too young. It's a rude reminder that life is very unpredictable, as unpredictable as the ball coming out of that legendary wrist of Shane Warne. Keep guessing.

That concludes the proceedings for the first day of this Test series. A tired Australian team will return to the hotel rooms and will try to recover after a hard day's play. One man though will have his phone ringing all evening and that's Imam-ul-Haq. What a day it was for him! He would look to continue with the good work on Saturday as well. The first ball will be at 10.30 am IST (5 am GMT) but as usual, our build-up will begin in advance. Until then, it's goodbye and cheers!

Imam-ul-Haq, the star of the day, comes up for a quick chat. He thanks his parents and the Almighty. Tells us that he has been working hard and he wanted to make this opportunity count. Says that he believes in the process and it's been a great game so far. Praises the team and also the camp they had in Karachi. Mentions that he played his last Test against Australia in Australia and was the 12th man for quite some time. On getting his first ton in Pakistan, Imam replies that these are the moments you play for. Says that you learn from your mistakes but cannot doubt yourself and need to believe in your abilities. Adds that he has played against Lyon who is a quality bowler and hitting him down the ground is his go-to shot. Shares that he has practised hard in the nets. Mentions that their main goal is to get back playing regularly in Pakistan and play some good cricket.

Pakistan made full use of winning the toss and batted with great control. The openers put together a century stand and then the pair of Azhar Ali and Imam-ul-Haq kept Australia at bay for two sessions. Their stand is worth 140 runs and Imam has also notched up his maiden Test hundred. Both these batters are looking good for more and with the kind of batters to follow, the signs are ominous for Australia if they don't strike early on Day 2.

Australia cannot be faulted for not trying. They stuck to their plans, bowled disciplined lines but there was nothing on offer from the pitch. Nathan Lyon received some support in the morning as the ball gripped and turned with extra bounce but it didn't last for long. Pat Cummins tried everything in his capacity, used as many as 8 overs but nothing worked out. The Aussies would have hoped for a breakthrough late in the day with the second new ball but that also didn't come and they ended the day's play with a solitary wicket.

1 wicket in 90 overs - Welcome to Pakistan after 24 years, Australia! A highly-anticipated Test series but the first day turned out to be fairly one-sided due to the docile nature of the pitch. Bat dominated proceedings on Day 1 and Pakistan benefitted by winning the toss. Imam-ul-Haq walks back with his head high. A good gesture from Usman Khawaja as he pats him on the back. A few Aussies also applaud him. The Pakistan dressing room is out to receive Imam. Great day for the Pakistan opener.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Azhar Ali defends it safely towards mid on. That will be Stumps on Day 1.
One ball left...
Full, outside off, spinning back in. Azhar defends it out.
Tossed up, on middle. Blocked out.
Another single as Imam-ul-Haq bunts it to mid-wicket.
A flatter ball, outside off. Azhar prods and hits it to backward point for a single.
Tossed up, on middle, it is pushed back to Lyon.
A short ball, angling on middle. Imam sits under it. Mitchell Starc looks exhausted now but has a cheeky smile as well.
On the pads, Azhar works it to square leg for a single.
Length ball, on off, pushed to covers.
A length ball, on middle. Blocked out on the leg side.
A length ball, on the pads, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Full and on middle. Imam looks to push on the off side but plays it off the inner half to mid on.
A quicker ball, down the leg side. Azhar tickles it straight to short fine leg.
Shorter ball, outside off. Azhar has a poke at it but misses.
Flatter ball, outside off. Azhar keeps it out.
Full ball, on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller and on middle. Imam wrists it to mid-wicket for a single.
Floated, full and on off. Imam steps across and tucks it to short leg.
Short of a length, on off. Azhar hops and taps it to gully.
A length ball, around off. Azhar solidly defends it on the off side.
Fuller ball, outside off. Azhar drives it straight to mid off.
Change in plans. David Warner moves to leg slip.
A length ball, angling outside off. Azhar leaves it alone.
A short ball now, on middle. Azhar dodges it.
A length ball, around off. Ali gets his bat down to block it.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Imam, with a big stride forward, as he blocks it out.
Fuller and on middle. Azhar flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
On middle, kept out.
The artificial light is switched on. Anyway, this could be the last over...
Slants a full ball, on the pads. Imam looks to tuck it but gets an inside edge to fine leg for a single.
Short and outside off. Left alone.
Imam tries to dominate the spinner! Tossed up, on off. Imam comes down the track and looks to smash it but mistimes it back to Lyon.
Nathan Lyon (28-4-82-1) is back into the attack. He could get some grip with the new ball.
Full and outside off, pushed to mid off. Another over safely negotiated.
This time Azhar does not chase this delivery outside the off stump.
Swing and a miss! A length ball, outside off. Azhar, without any foot movement, looks to push but misses.
On middle, on a length. Blocked out.
On a good length around off. Azhar gets inside the line of the ball and defends it back.
Another length ball, outside off. Azhar shoulders arms to it.
A length ball, around off. Imam with yet another block.
A full ball, around leg, swinging away from the left-hander. Imam shuffles but misses his flick. Good take from Alex Carey behind.
Same line as the previous delivery. Imam is happy to keep it out.
Slower one, length and on middle. Defended out.
Sliding around middle. Azhar nudges it through mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Punched to covers.
Josh Hazlewood (13-3-23-0) to share the second new cherry from the other end.
Not much movement with the new ball for Starc! On middle, it is flicked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A length ball, outside off. Imam knocks it to deep point and rotates the strike.
Much better! Near to the off stump line, fullish delivery. Imam pushes it with the full face of the bat to mid off.
Starc is missing his line here. Length ball, way wide outside off. Imam offers no shot.
A length ball, outside off. Imam watches it go through to the keeper.
Starc starts with a full ball, outside off, a little bit of swing. Imam looks to push with gentle hands but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
SECOND NEW BALL IS TAKEN! Mitchell Starc (12-2-39-0) returns to make the first use of it.
Outside off. Azhar leaves it alone.
A dipping yorker now, on middle. Azhar gets his bat down in time to defend it.
Beautiful shot but for no run. A length ball, outside off. Azhar punches off the back foot to covers. Marnus Labuschagne with a good stop this time.
Outside off, on a length. Left alone.
Fuller ball, around off. Azhar drives it nicely to the right of mid off but the fielder there dives to stop it.
Length ball, outside off. Ali taps it with soft hands to point.
Angles it on the pads, it is flicked to square leg.
On middle, fuller and Imam defends it out.

FOUR! Edgy runs! Floated, around off, it lands and turns away. Imam prods to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes past first slip to the third man fence. Usman Khawaja gives a chase but to no avail. Now then, this delivery might just prompt Australia to further delay the second new ball.
Full ball again, on middle. Imam lunges as he defends this out.
Tossed up, full and on middle. Blocked out.
Fuller ball, on middle. Azhar drills it to long on for a single.
The second new ball is available! Australia though have decided to not take it immediately. Nathan Lyon to continue...

Fuller delivery, on middle, Azhar eases it off his pads with good timing and it races away past mid on. Starc gives the chase, slides near the fence and stops it from crossing the fence. They get three runs.
Yorker outside off, this time Imam digs it out wide of the point fielder and collects a single.
Lands it very full and outside off, Imam reaches out and squeezes it to point.
Too full and close to off, Imam brings down a straight bat and keeps it out towards mid on.
Uses the angle of the bowler and works a full ball towards mid-wicket.
Starts from 'round the wicket and delivers it on a length around off, Imam stays back to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
The new ball is handed over to the umpire. Still one over to go before Australia can claim it. Meanwhile, Cameron Green (3-0-14-0) is back into the attack.
Fullish and on off, Azhar plays a punchy drive off the front foot but finds the cover fielder.
Drags his length short and delivers it on off, Imam goes on the back foot and punches it to long on for one.
Fuller and on off, Ali uses his feet and forces it down to long on for a run.
Lunges to a full ball and bunts it back to the bowler.
A bit short and around leg, defended from the back foot to short leg.
Loopy and full around leg, it's defended back to the bowler.
Short and wide outside off, hammered to sweeper cover for one.
A touch short around off, turning down, Imam moves back and works it through square leg for a run.
Slower through the air, full and around off, Imam walks forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
A full toss outside off, it's struck firmly down to long off for one.
Azhar goes straighter this time and drives a full ball down to long off for a single.
Full and flighted outside off, Ali drives but finds covers.
Drags his length short and delivers it on off, Imam rocks back and punches it towards short cover.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Fuller around leg, flicked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Chance? Quicker and flatter, around leg, Azhar flicks it across the line. It takes the inner half, brushes the pads but doesn't carry to Warner at leg gully.
A slider around middle and leg, it's nudged down to fine leg for a single.
Flighted and close to off, Imam defends it near his front pad.
Fuller and around off, defended back.
Another freebie, a full toss around middle, Imam just buys a single by pulling it to deep mid-wicket.
A friendly full toss on middle, Imam-ul-Haq defends it back to the bowler.
Short outside off, spinning away, cut through point for a single.
Flatter and shorter around off, Ali goes back and punches to the off side. Smith moves to his left to make the stop.
Good landing from Smudge. Full and around leg, Azhar gets forward and drives it to mid off.
Some more spin as Steven Smith is introduced into the attack.
Flighted and full, around off, Imam-ul-Haq strides forward and blocks.
Skidding down leg, Imam goes back and taps it down in front of short leg.
FOUR! That's a wonderful shot! Full and floated, around off and turning away, Imam wears his skates, makes room and lofts it cleanly over extra cover for a boundary.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
A touch short in length, on middle, Imam goes back and punches it towards mid-wicket. Steps out for a run but then returns.
Fuller and on the pads, Imam helps it towards short leg.
Walks down the track to a full ball and knocks it down to long on for one. All too easy.
Drags his length short, outside off, Imam-ul-Haq cracks it to sweeper cover for a brace.
Gets behind the line and defends it back.

FIFTY FOR AZHAR! His 6th against Australia in Tests! You can see the confidence since he has been out there. Calm and composed. Full and floated, outside off, Ali strokes it down to long off for one. He too would be eyeing a hundred here.
Very full and on off, Imam drills it down to long on for one.
Flighted and full, outside off, Imam drives it back and Marnus dives across to his left to stop the ball.
Quicker one again, around leg, Azhar plays it in front of his pads and works it to short mid-wicket.
Flatter one, on the pads, played towards short leg.
Full and flighted, around off, Ali strides forward and drives it down through mid off. The long on fielder cuts it off and he gets a couple. Moves to 49!
Flatter and a bit shorter around off, from 'round the wicket, Azhar goes back and pushes it to point.
Lyon pulls his length back a bit, serves it around middle and off, Imam goes back and punches it to long off for a single.
Fuller and around leg, Imam is on the front foot and defends it back to the bowler.

CENTURY STAND! Loopy and full, around leg, Imam wrists it behind square leg and takes a single. This has been a great association between Azhar Ali and Imam-ul-Haq, both have blunted Australia's bowling fairly easily.
Tossed up outside off, forced down to long off for one.
Too full on this occasion, around off, it's eased down to long on for a single.
Fullish and outside off, slower through the air, Imam presses forward and pushes it to covers.
Good flight on this one too, it lands full around middle, Imam clears his front leg and defends.
A bit of extra flight, landing full around off, Ali drives it down to long off and picks up a single.
Full and around off, defended off the front foot.
Walks forward to a full ball and knocks it down to long on for a run.
Floated and full around middle, Azhar opens up in his stance as he defends it down.
Loopy and full outside off, Ali draws forward and defends it towards point.
Strides forward to a full ball and defends it back to the bowler.
Turning down the leg side, Azhar tries to flick but misses.

Drinks break. The search for a breakthrough continues for the touring team. The current stand is nearing 100 and it has kept Australia at bay easily in the last session. Imam-ul-Haq has completed his maiden Test hundred and wants more. 20 overs left in the day's play.
200 up for Pakistan! Outside off again with some away turn as well. Azhar hits it past point for a single.
Flighted ball, on off. Ali defends it out.
Labuschagne getting some turn here! Flatter, outside off, turning away from the right-hander. Azhar has a poke at it but misses.
Tossed up, on middle. Blocked out.
Fuller ball, on off, pushed to point.
A loosener from Marnus Labuschagne! Short one, leg breaker, around off. Imam gently turns it to mid-wicket for a single.
Marnus Labuschagne returns to bowl his second over. He claims to have dismissed Steven Smith in the nets, let's see if he can do some magic with his leggies.
A floated ball, on middle, Azhar gets forward as he hits it back to Lyon.
Full and on middle, drilled down to long on for a single.
Angles a full ball, on middle, Imam gets an outside edge as he looks to defend. The ball dribbles to point.
Another solid front foot defense from Azhar Ali.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Imam lunges to defend it.
On middle, pushed to mid on.
On a length, outside off. Imam punches it to deep point and keeps the strike.
A length ball, swinging in, around off. Imam, on the front foot, defends it.
Short of a length, on middle. Imam hops and blocks it on the leg side.
A length ball, outside off. Azhar plays it with soft hands and steers it to third man for a single.
A length ball, tailing on the pads. Imam looks to flick but gets an inside edge through square leg for one.
Fuller ball, around off, slight inward movement there. Imam blocks it back to Starc.
Tossed up, full ball on middle. Azhar blocks it out.
Again Azhar hits it back to Lyon.
Tossed up, outside off. Ali plays it back to the bowler.
Around off, defended to covers.
Darted on the pads, it is flicked to deep square leg for a single.
A full ball, very full, on middle, Imam defends it out.
Fullish delivery, angling wide outside off. Left alone.
A full ball, around off. Imam defends it towards the gully region, with soft hands and takes a quick single.
Touch fuller, around off. Imam punches it to mid on.

FOUR! Maiden Test hundred for Imam-ul-Haq! Just a check drive as he hits it through covers and the ball races away to the fence. Imam jumps in celebration, a bit like David Warner does. He has a big smile on his face. Goes down on the pitch to do a 'Sajda' and thanks the Almighty. Relief writ large on his face. A crucial century for Imam's career. He has fallen out of favour recently due to his injuries and ordinary form and there was a debate regarding him playing in the XI over Shan Masood too, but Imam has vindicated the decision of the team management to open with him. Hundred is just a landmark, he should be thinking about a big one here.
Imam-ul-Haq is looking nervous now! He tries to chase this wayward delivery and fails to get any bat on it.
On a length, on middle. Defended out back on the deck.
Slightly short, around off. Imam punches it to deep cover and retains the strike. Three away from his maiden ton in Test cricket.
Flighted on middle, Imam prods and blocks it out.
Tossed up, full and on off. Imam plays it late as he blocks it to short leg.
Fuller and on middle. Blocked out.
Three taken! Very full and outside off. Azhar steps forward and drives it through covers. Cummins gives a long chase, dives near the ropes and saves a single.
Starts with a flatter one, quicker and on middle, Ali hits it to mid-wicket.
Change from both ends. Nathan Lyon (19-4-59-1) is back into the attack.
Good start to the new spell by Starc. A length ball, outside off. Imam shoulders arms to it.
This one is down the leg side and Imam fails to connect with his attempted flick shot.
On a length, on middle, Imam tucks it to square leg. Not in the gap. Stays on 96!
Length and on off. Imam taps it to point. Body language is very important in this game and at the moment, Imam is getting frustrated. Nervous 90s.
Full ball, outside off, asking Imam to drive and he does go for it but loses his shape while positioning himself and fails to connect with his shot. He has a nervous smile on his face.
On middle, on a length, this is flicked to mid-wicket.
Change in bowling. As expected, Mitchell Starc returns to bowl now. 0 for 31 in his 9 overs thus far.

Full ball, coming straight with the angle, on middle. Azhar closes the face of the bat as he tries to work it on the leg side but gets a leading edge to covers. Luckily for him, it went all along the ground.
A single! Short of a length, outside off. Imam dabs it to third man for a run.
Full ball, outside off, it jags back in. Imam pushes off the inner half of the blade to mid on.
Mitchell Starc is loosening up, maybe getting ready for one final burst with the old ball.
Fuller and on off. Imam, on the front foot, defends it.
Drags his length back but the line is the same. Imam nudges it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, on middle, Imam works it straight to the fielder at mid-wicket.
Short in length, on middle. Imam bunts it to square leg for an easy single. He is five runs away from his century.
On the pads, this is tucked to deep square leg for one.
Slightly full, on off. Blocked out.
Full and wide outside off, this is hit to covers.
Josh slants a length ball on the pads, Imam flicks it to deep square leg and looks for a couple of runs but Azhar is quick to deny the second run. Good fielding in the deep.
On a length, on off. Imam defends it solidly.
Short in length, on middle. Imam-ul-Haq hops and tucks it behind square on the leg side for a run, his first after the Tea break.
Touch fuller, outside off. Imam knocks it to mid off.
A length ball, around off. Imam defends from the back foot.
Cummins goes wide of the crease and angles a short ball, on middle. Imam leans back, sits under it and lets it through.
On a  length, on middle. Blocked out.
Fuller ball, on middle, Imam mistimes his push back to the bowler.
Around off, on a length, defended off the front foot.
Close to off, on a fuller length, it's pushed away gently to short cover.
Josh cooks a bouncer around off, Azhar Ali quickly goes down and ducks.
Lands it on a length and outside off, at 131.4 kph, Azhar defends it from the back foot to the off side.
Fuller delivery, around off and angling in, Azhar lunges and blocks it near his front pad.

FOUR! Finds the gap superbly! Back of a length, around off, Azhar hangs on the back foot and punches it through the line. There are two fielders in a catching position at short cover but Ali pierces the gap between them and finds the fence.
Cummins bends his back to go short, it's around off and Imam is on his toes as he jams it down.
Very full in length again, around off, Imam drills his drive through the line but finds the cover fielder.
Bumper around leg, Imam ducks underneath it.
Very full and on off, Imam plays a punchy drive down the ground and the mid on fielder rushes across to his right to make the stop.
Cummins pulls his length back a shade, delivers it around off, angling in, Imam is solidly behind the line in defense.
Delivers it full and outside off, Imam covers the line and shoulders arms.
On a good length and outside off, Ali goes back and across as he defends it to the off side.
Fuller and angling towards off, Ali is forward and defends it near his front pad.
Serves it close to off, again Ali defends it watchfully.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.

FOUR! That's delightful. Josh Hazlewood overpitches around off, trying to bring the two catchers on the off side into play, but Azhar leans forward and drives along the ground through extra cover for a boundary.
Fuller and closer to off, as usual, Hazlewood is right on the money, Azhar defends it to the off side.
Josh Hazlewood to bowl from the other end.
Cummins keeps probing around off, lands it on a good length, Imam-ul-Haq sticks back and defends it to the off side.
Slightly short in length, around off, Imam goes on the back foot and pushes it towards short mid-wicket.
Landing on a length and angling in around off, Imam is again forward as he blocks it safely.
Serves it on a length around off, Imam is behind the line as he defends it back solidly.
Angles in a full ball around off, Imam pushes it from the middle of his bat to mid on.
Cummins begins from 'round the wicket and delivers it on a good length outside off, Imam shoulders arms.
We are back for the final session. The players walk out to the middle. Imam-ul-Haq and Azhar Ali to continue their innings. Pat Cummins to start after the break...
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

Another session belonging to Pakistan! They scored 66 runs in it and more importantly, didn't lose a single wicket. Australia toiled hard but without any success. Imam-ul-Haq has prospered after a watchful start and played some delightful strokes in the afternoon. He is 8 shy of his maiden Test hundred and would be hoping to get there immediately. Azhar Ali partnered him well, mixing caution with a little bit of aggression and together this pair kept the touring team at bay. It's a docile surface and Australia can't do much. They have to keep trying and stay patient. Discipline will be key for them in the last session where the bowlers will start to tire out. Do join us at 3.50 pm IST (10.20 am GMT) for the final session.
Flatter and on off, knocked down to long on for a run. That will be TEA ON DAY 1!
FOUR! Imam moves into the 90s! A low full toss wide outside off, Imam strides forward and crunches it through covers. It finds the fence, beating Khawaja's dive near the boundary line.
Floated and around off, turning back in, Imam goes inside the crease and plays it down in front of short leg.
Very full and around off, Imam drives it back to the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Azhar drives it through mid off and takes a single.
Great landing from a part-timer. Full and around off, Ali defends it with the turn to the off side.
Change in bowling. Marnus Labuschagne to bowl his leggies.
Action replay of the previous delivery, again Imam bends his knee to go down low as he evades.
Bouncer outside off, Imam crouches, leans back a bit and allows it through.
A touch short and around middle, Ali uses the angle and works it to deep square leg for a run.
Pitches it up and outside off, Ali drives it from the middle of his bat but finds the cover fielder.
Full again, around off, Azhar shows a straight bat and keeps it out safely to covers.
Full and angling in around off, defended to the off side.

FOUR! Even better. Just a check-drive and it has gone to the fence. Starc delivers it on a length and outside off, clocking 140 clicks, Imam leans into the drive and transfers his weight into the shot. The placement is crisp through covers and it's back-to-back boundaries for Imam who will be smelling his maiden Test hundred.

FOUR! Shot! The idea from the bowler was right but the execution is not quite there. An attempted yorker turns out to be a juicy low full toss on middle, Imam keeps his balance and flicks it beautifully through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Sprays it full and wide outside off, inviting the batter to chase, Imam has nothing to do with it.
Delivers it on a good length, close to off, Imam is on the back foot as he blocks it down safely.
Fuller and around leg, clipped to deep mid-wicket for a single.
On a length around off, not moving in much, Azhar defends it back from the crease.
Pitches it up and around off, at 136.1 kph, Imam leans across and pushes it down to mid on.
Back of a length, outside off and leaving the left-hander with the angle, Imam offers no shot.

Josh goes short, around off at 140.1 kph, Azhar obliges with a pull shot, rolls his wrists over the ball and sends it all along the ground to deep square leg for a single. The 50-run stand has come up!
Fuller this time, around off at 132.4 kph, Azhar Ali prods forward and pushes it defensively to covers.
Fractionally short and around off, tailing back in a shade at 129 kph, Azhar is on the back foot as he punches it to covers.
