Fuller in length, around off, Azhar defends it to covers and yells a loud 'no'.
A touch short and on middle at 136 clicks, shooting up off the surface, Imam uses all his height to ride the bounce as he defends it towards square leg.
Fractionally short and around leg, Azhar goes on his toes and glances it behind square leg for one.
Fuller and on middle, Ali stays on the back foot and defends it towards mid on.

FOUR! Eased away! This outfield gives you value for your shots. Starc loses his radar, serves a length ball on the pads and Azhar nudges it to fine leg. The ball races away and finds the fence, beating the diving effort of Nathan Lyon.
Darts in a very full ball outside off, Azhar gets forward and keeps it out safely.
Bowls it with a slingy action, delivers it full and outside off, Imam drives it on the up and sends it through point for a single.
Mitchell Starc (7-1-16-0) is back on. Will we get to see some reverse swing going?
Fuller and close to off, a bit of movement there, Ali defends it to the off side by pressing forward.
Hazlewood gets this one to angle in, from a length around off at 132.3 kph, Azhar presents a dead bat in defense.
A gentle length delivery, in the region outside off and going straight on with the seam, Azhar drops his wrists and allows it through.
Drifting down the leg side, with the angle of the bowler, Imam tucks it to deep square leg for one.
Full and around off, defended again, off the front foot.
Starts with a length ball outside off, Imam plays it down defensively to covers.
Josh Hazlewood (7-3-9-0) is back for another spell.
Very full and outside off. Azhar steps across to keep it out.
On middle, fuller and blocked by Azhar on the surface.
Tossed up, on off. Ali lunges to defend it towards covers. They wanted a single but denied it in the end.
Flatter, straight on middle. Azhar gets inside the line and defends it.
Flighted ball, around off. Imam-ul-Haq works it to point for another single.
Very full and on middle, pushed to mid on.
Azhar Ali with another leave to end the over.
Down the leg side. Left alone.
FOUR! Azhar Ali with yet another beautiful stroke! Short of a length, on middle. Azhar Ali swivels and pulls it to deep backward square leg for a boundary. Finds the gap really well.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.

A big shout for caught behind but not given! Mostly from Steven Smith at first slip! Green again angles it down the leg side. Azhar Ali looks to flick it but misses. The keeper collects it but the appeal is not entertained.
Short ball, directed down the leg side. Ali shoulders arms to it.
Shorter and outside off. Ali drops it to covers for one run.
Full and on off. Defended out.

SIX! Azhar makes the most of it. Tossed up ball, on middle. Azhar gets low and slog-sweeps it towards deep mid-wicket for a biggie. There was a fielder stationed but it was well wide. It is taken upstairs to check and the replay shows it went over the fence. Very sure, Azhar only intended to get a boundary but he ended up timing it too well.
Fuller and on middle. Azhar lunges and blocks it out.
Tossed up, on off. Azhar shuffles across and defends it out.
Floated ball, outside off. Azhar bunts it to the leg side.

Drinks break. Another passage of play where Australia struggled to create a breakthrough. 30 runs scored during a period of 12 overs and both the batters are looking at ease. The touring team will have to stay patient and keep trying hard. Pakistan's plan will be to stay focused, preserve wickets and score runs at the same time.
FOUR! Lovely shot! A length ball, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq goes back and drives it through covers for a boundary.
On middle. Blocked out.
Short of a length, on middle. It gets big on Imam-ul-Haq as he defends it uppishly on the leg side. It's called a no ball.
Length ball, angling on middle, extra bounce there. Azhar nudges it to fine leg for one more. A late no ball given as well.
Short of a length, on middle. Imam-ul-Haq wrists it to deep square leg for a single.
Shorter and on middle, Imam-ul-Haq ducks underneath it.
A length ball, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq looks to defend but gets an outside edge to the point region. There was a single available but Azhar Ali turned down the call.
Angles a flatter ball, on middle, Azhar shuffles and turns it to mid-wicket.
Shorter ball, outside off, cut away to deep point for a single.
This is way outside off and Imam-ul-Haq makes yet another leave.
Fuller ball, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq offers no shot.
Outside off, left alone.
Tossed up, outside off. Azhar prods to defend but it takes the outer half of the blade, towards covers for a single.
Length ball, on middle, Imam-ul-Haq tries to flick but gets beaten on the inside edge and gets hit high on the pads. The ball rolls back on the deck and goes wide of the stumps.
On a length, on middle. Imam-ul-Haq stays back as he works it on the leg side.
On middle, tucked through mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball, on the pads. Azhar flicks it wide of mid-wicket and collects a couple of runs before Nathan Lyon cuts it off.
Bangs a bouncer now, well over Azhar as he ducks under it.
Green serves a length ball, drifting down the leg side. Ali misses his flick.
Cameron Green is introduced into the attack now. He is a tall man and surely will get some extra bounce from the surface.
Shorter, outside off, not much spin there and Imam-ul-Haq makes an easy leave.
A single as Azhar Ali pushes it wide of long on.
Tossed up, on middle. Azhar defends it on the leg side.
Flatter and on middle. Blocked out.

Tossed up, fuller and on middle, Imam-ul-Haq once again aims to send it flying over long on but only manage to force it down the ground, all along the carpet. The long off fielder cuts it off and they get just a single.
SIX! BANG! A flighted ball, full and on off, Imam-ul-Haq comes down the track and hammers it over long on for a biggie.
On a length, around middle. Azhar Ali keeps it out.
Touch fuller, outside off, Azhar knocks it to covers.
A length ball, on middle, Imam-ul-Haq pushes it to the right of mid on and takes a quick single.
Length ball, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone.
On a length, slanting on middle. Imam-ul-Haq is solid in his back-foot defense.
Length ball, on the pads. Azhar clips it to the fine leg region for a single.
Fuller ball, outside off, pushed straight to the fielder at covers.
Tossed up, on middle. Imam-ul-Haq prods and defends it.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Fuller and on the pads, defended back.
Short and on off, Imam gets back and taps it down to point.

A huge appeal for LBW but not given! Confusion there regarding the DRS, Carey and Lyon have a word, Smith also gestures from first slip. Where is the captain? Pat Cummins is at mid on. He comes forward, asking whether to take or not. Eventually, his gesture suggests that it's too high and no DRS has been taken. In fact, they have run out of time. Coming to the delivery, it's flighted and around off, landing and shooting off the surface, Imam gets across in defense but misses to get hit on the back thigh. The Ball Tracking shows that it's clipping the top of the off stump.
Length ball, outside off. Azhar blocks it towards point.
Short of a length, on off. Azhar hops and blocks it.
Cummins continues to shuffle his length. This time it is short and on middle. Azhar first thinks to pull but eventually evades it. Lovely bowling.
Length ball, nipping back in, outside off. Azhar gets his bat down and defends it.
Another short ball from Cummins, outside off this time. Azhar ducks under it.
A short ball, angling on middle. Ali sits under it.
A single to end then! On the pads, this is clipped through mid-wicket for one.
Flatter and on middle, Ali flicks it to mid-wicket.
Another run as this is nudged on the leg side.
The line is a straighter one, Ali works it through square leg and gets to the other end.
Shorter and on off, this is punched through covers for one.
Shorter and on off, Imam rocks back and pushes it to covers.
Good tight stuff from the Aussies after the break! On off, Ali keeps it out.
In the air... safe! On the shorter side, Ali looks to work it on the leg side, closes the face of the bat early, it goes off the leading edge but lands safely on the off side.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Good length and outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and on middle, Imam stands tall and defends.
Goes short and on the body, Imam ducks under it.
Slightly shorter and on off, Ali pushes it to covers.
Full and flighted on off, Imam runs down the track and lofts it over mid off. There is a fielder in the deep and hence only a single.
Tossed up, above the eye line. It lands in the line of the stumps, Imam comes forward and plays it onto the ground.
Another one floated up on off, kept out.
On middle, Imam-ul-Haq leans forward in defense.
Imam steps out but gets too close to the pitch of the ball, he jams it back to the bowler.
On middle, defended.
Good length and on middle, blocked.
Angled into the middle pole, Ali shows the full face of the bat and strokes it to mid on.
Good length and on off, defended.
Imam now scores his first run of this session! Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
First run of this session! Good length and on off, this is guided through point for one.
Pat Cummins to bowl from the other end!
Shorter and on off, Imam pushes it to covers. A maiden to begin.
Loopy ball on off, Imam-ul-Haq leans forward and blocks it out.
Gives it air again and bowls it on middle, kept out.

Update - In a nerve-wracking opener of the ICC Women's World Cup 2022, Deandra Dottin has pulled a rabbit out of the hat in the final over where New Zealand Women needed 6 runs off 6 balls. Three wickets in the last over and West Indies Women have started their campaign by upsetting the host nation.
Three good balls to begin with! Floats it up yet again, lands it on middle, defended.
Gives it air and lands it on off, Imam-ul-Haq lunges and keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Imam-ul-Haq defends.

We are back for the afternoon session! The Australian players make their way out to the middle and are followed by the two batters Imam-ul-Haq and Azhar Ali who will continue their innings. Nathan Lyon, the only man to take a wicket, will begin after the break.
... DAY 1, SESSION 2 ...

As expected, it's been hard work for the Aussies on this unresponsive pitch. There wasn't much zip with the new ball although Nathan Lyon got some good turn and bounce. The Pakistan openers successfully blunted the offie with their sensible approach. Australia recognized early that picking wickets won't be easy and worked well as a unit to dry up the runs but after the Drinks break, Pakistan pressed on the accelerator and scored quite freely. The pitch is only going to get better for batting from here on and the touring team will have to be on the money with its plans. Do join us at 2 pm IST (8.30 am GMT) for the post-Lunch session.

A wicket at the stroke of Lunch and the food will taste slightly better for Australia. It was a laboured session for them where they tried hard but without any success until the last moment. Overall, Pakistan owned the morning session courtesy of a strong opening stand between Abdullah Shafique and Imam-ul-Haq. The former started positively and the latter took some time to settle down. Once Imam got his eye in, he batted fluently and is looking good for a big score. Abdullah would be quite disappointed after throwing away his wicket on a placid surface.
The last ball is negotiated well! Length and on off, this one actually zips off the surface. Ali plays it with soft hands and it goes to gully. That will be the end of a long session. LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Fuller and on middle, this is played back to the bowler.
Sharp stuff! A bumper on middle, Ali evades it. That was pacy.
Another one on a length and on off, blocked.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.
Azhar Ali walks out to bat!

OUT! TAKEN! That is an outstanding catch from Cummins! Nathan Lyon gets the wicket Australia so desperately needed. Abdullah Shafique walks back 6 short of a half ton. He probably wanted to get to the milestone quickly. That perhaps was playing on his mind. Looks to get to it with one hit. Steps out, Lyon drags the length back just a little. Abdullah Shafique still looks to go big, he does go with the turn but there is extra bounce which Lyon usually gets. It goes off the top edge towards mid on. Cummins, from mid off, runs there and takes a tumbling catch. A wicket at the stroke of Lunch. Just what they would have wanted. They do have time for another one.
Commentary.Howout: c Pat Cummins b Nathan Lyon

Commentary.Commentary: Quicker and slightly shorter, defended.
Flatter and on middle, kept out.
Tossed up on off, defended.

Uppish but just wide! Lovely delivery. Floats it up. Abdullah Shafique steps out, the ball dips into the batter at the end, turns back in. Abdullah Shafique looks to drive it through the off side, it goes off the inner half, uppishly, past the mid-wicket fielder for two.
Steps out now and eases it down to long off for one.
On a length outside off, left alone.
Starc serves it on a length around leg, Abdullah gets squared up slightly as he defends it to the off side.
The physio is tending to Imam-ul-Haq. He has hurt his fingers and needs the magic of the magic spray. All is good now and we resume...
Ouch! Extra bounce from a good length around middle, Imam goes back to glance but it shoots up to ping him on the gloves. The ball rolls behind in the direction of fine leg and they cross.
Fullish and on off, Imam brings his bat down and defends it towards mid on.
Short in length, around off and angling away again, this time Abdullah Shafique gets the opportunity to go on the back foot and ease it through point for an easy run.
Beaten all ends up! Starc darts across a full ball, landing close to off and skidding away with the angle, Abdullah Shafique is lured into the drive and gets beaten comprehensively.
Pitches it on a length around leg, Imam is solidly behind the line as he blocks it towards mid-wicket.
Digs it in short, around off and angling away, Imam leans back and allows it through to the keeper.
On a length, around middle and off, Imam-ul-Haq sits back and defends it to mid-wicket.

Here comes the century partnership now! Short in length, around off, Abdullah Shafique swivels on the back foot and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single. The crowd seems very happy and it's a great start for the hosts.
On a length and around off, Abdullah Shafique defends it solidly to the off side.
Lands it full and around off, Abdullah Shafique defends it off the inside edge to the leg side. Pat is quick to get to the ball and disallows the 100th run to Pakistan.
Fuller in length on middle, Imam drives down the ground but straight to mid on.

Starc goes short again, outside off and angling away, Abdullah Shafique stands back to cut but it gets away off the bottom edge. The ball drops near the pitch and Imam-ul-Haq calls his partner through for a single.
Short and down the leg side, Abdullah Shafique tries glancing as an afterthought and misses.

FOUR! Classy! Mitchell Starc is a little too full with his length and it's around middle and leg, Abdullah Shafique leans across and flicks it delightedly through the gap between mid-wicket and mid on for a boundary.
Back of a length, close to off, at 134.4 kph, Imam goes on his toes and drops it with soft hands on the off side. It's wide of the cover fielder and they steal a single.
Starts by spearing in a very full ball around off, Imam-ul-Haq flicks it slightly aerially but wide of mid on.
Mitchell Starc is back for another burst. 0 for 8 in his 4 overs so far.
Cummins keeps his length full and lands it close to off, Shafique defends it to the off side.
Full and on off, at 135.3 kph, Abdullah Shafique is solid in his defense.
This time Abdullah Shafique connects with his drive to a fuller ball but it goes back to Pat Cummins.
A muted appeal for a catch, nothing doing. Full and around off, shaping away a tad, Abdullah Shafique is not entirely forward as he tries to drive down the ground but misses.

Slightly short and around off, Abdullah Shafique stays back and pushes it with an angled bat towards covers. The fielder fails to stop with a slide and the ball travels to the deep. They collect a couple.
Around off, on a length, Imam-ul-Haq inside-edges his attempted forward defense. It rolls behind square leg for one.
Slower one, down the leg side, Abdullah Shafique lets it be.
Bouncer, ducked easily by Abdullah Shafique.

Shout for a run out, not entertained by the square leg umpire. Josh Hazlewood is again fuller and this time the line is around off, Imam tries to defend but it takes the inner edge and goes behind square leg. They cross for a run and there is a direct hit at the striker's end by Marnus Labuschagne. He though doesn't show a lot of excitement in appeal and knowing him, that has to be absolutely not out then.
Josh Hazlewood changes his length and goes fuller on this occasion, outside off, there to be driven, Imam shows restrain and lets it go.
Back of a length, around off, Imam is on the back foot and he offers a dead bat in defense.
Josh speeds in from 'round the wicket and hurls across a length ball outside off, Imam has nothing to do with it.
Another single to end! Runs continue to come by for the hosts! On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
On off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it through covers and gets to the other end.
Angled into the pads, Imam works it down to fine leg for one.
On middle, Imam defends.
Almost chops it on! Cummins goes short again, extra bounce this time. Imam looks to defend but gets an inside edge which lands just around the off pole.

FOUR! Fifty for Imam-ul-Haq! Back in the side and back amongst the runs. Solid from him. He weathered the storm earlier and once he got his eye in, has scored freely. A big score is on the offer here. Gets there by welcoming Cummins with a boundary. This is short and on middle, it is pulled through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Change! The skipper, Pat Cummins, brings himself on now.
Another solid defensive stroke to this ball on off.
Lands it on a length yet again, kept out.
Short and on middle, Abdullah Shafique sways away from it.
Good length and on middle, defended.
Angled into middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Good length and on off, Abdullah Shafique looks to drop and run but is sent back.
Floats it up on off, blocked.
On middle, defended.

FOUR! Put away! This has been the problem for Lyon. He has bowled a boundary ball in almost all of his overs. After three dots, he fails to keep the pressure, bowls a half-tracker and outside off, Imam goes back and cuts it through point. Another boundary will see him get to his fifty.
Gives it air yet again and lands it on off, blocked.
Floats it up on off, defended.
Flatter and on the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.

Angled into the pads, this is clipped to mid-wicket. A maiden then by Josh Hazlewood! Australia once again need to put a lid on the scoring here. All the pressure that was built early on has been released by the spinners who have just not been at their best.
Angled into the middle pole, Abdullah Shafique plays it to mid on.
This time, he hangs back as the length is shortened and plays it right under his eyes.
And again, it is more off a push and not a forward defense. Probably because he knows the ball won't be moving a lot now. On off, Shafique now firmly plays it to covers.
Very solid! Even the defensive strokes are played with a lot of confidence now. Length and on off, Abdullah Shafique puts in a good stride forward and pushes it to covers.
Good length and on middle, this is defended.
On middle, defended.

SIX! BANG! Imam is in his elements! He moves into the 40s with that massive hit! Once again, beautifully steps out and gets to the pitch of it, lofts the ball over the head of the bowler and over the long off fence.
A single as this is pushed through covers.
Floats it up on off, blocked.
Loopy ball on off, this is pushed to cover and Shafique wants a run but is sent back.
Tosses it up on off, defended.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Imam is dealing in boundaries for now! This is a gift for someone who has been there for more than 20 overs. Especially if you are from the subcontinent. On the pads, this is worked fine on the leg side and it races away to the fine leg fence. He has overtaken his partner now, after starting sedately.
On off, solidly defended.
Nothing for now though! This is on a length, just goes on with the angle, it is played to mid on.

Angled into middle, this is worked to mid-wicket. It will be interesting to see if the Aussies get some reverse swing. The conditions in Pakistan are ideal for reverse swing and that is probably when the Aussie pacers can come into use.
Good length and just outside off, left alone.
Change! Josh Hazlewood is back on now. Can he get the wicket for his side?
Flatter and quicker on off, defended.
Flatter and on the pads, Imam works it towards mid-wicket.
On the stumps, this is played back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it towards cover and takes one.
On middle, Abdullah Shafique works it to mid-wicket.
On off, this is blocked.
Really good from Imam! Solid, solid batting so far! This is floated up on off, Imam lunges and defends.
Flatter and on off, Imam pushes it to covers.
FOUR! Second boundary in the over and third in the last two for Imam! This is a gift, a half volley on the pads, it is flicked through mid-wicket, no one in the deep and another boundary results.
Another one quicker through the air and on off, blocked.
Flatter and on middle, Imam defends.
FOUR! Imam is really using his feet well. Also, runs have started to come now. He steps out and gets to the pitch of it this time, lofts it over mid on and it races away.
A dot to end! On off, gives it flight. Abdullah Shafique lunges and keeps it out.
On the stumps, defended solidly.
Floats it up on off, blocked.
Now follows the boundary with a single as this is worked with the angle through square leg for one.

FOUR! That is a very good shot! Really well played in the end! Imam steps out, he does not quite get to the pitch of the ball and it also turns away a little. He goes ahead with the shot, the good thing is, he plays it with the turn - over mid off for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle, defended.
On off, this is worked with the turn to mid on.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On off, kept out.
A single now as this is worked to mid-wicket.
On the stumps, blocked.
Flatter and on middle, defended.

Drinks break. Right then, Pakistan have successfully seen off the shine on the ball and have all their wickets intact. Both, Abdullah Shafique and Imam-ul-Haq have looked at ease at the crease and the former in particular has been more positive. The Aussie bowlers have laboured hard on a largely unresponsive wicket and have done well to keep the scoring rate under check. The spinners are getting some bite from the surface but so far there's nothing threatening. Will the picture change in the next passage of the play?

Another one which lands on middle, Abdullah Shafique is solid in defense. The round the wicket angle is a good one, it challenges both the edges. Lyon is also landing it well, around middle so that the one that goes on with the arm takes the outside edge and the one that turns in can catch the inside part.
On middle, Abdullah Shafique blocks it.
Turn and bounce! This pitches around leg, Shafique looks to flick but this one turns away and there is also extra bounce. Carey fails to collect it cleanly and it goes down to fine leg for two. Byes.
On the pads, this is worked to square leg.
Tossed up on off, this is pushed to cover for one.
On middle, this is worked down to long on for one.
On middle again, Imam works it to mid-wicket. Head was bowling a little too flat in this over, that is how he bowls but it is the tossed up balls that have gotten more purchase.
Floats it up on middle, defended.
Imam should have done better there! That is short and outside off, Imam cuts but straight to point.
Flatter and on off, defended.
FOUR! Slapped away! Travis Head drags his length short and bowls it wide outside off, Imam-ul-Haq immediately goes back and slaps it to the point fence. That's what you get by bowling a part-timer!
Starts well, lands a full ball around off, Imam is on the front foot in defense.
Interesting move from Pat Cummins. Travis Head to bowl now.
Floated and full, around off, Abdullah Shafique leans forward and defends it off the inner edge to short leg.
Turns it off his pads to square leg and takes a single.

Some spin there. Full and around off, Abdullah Shafique tries to defend with soft hands and gets an inside edge. It beats the leg gully fielder and races behind to fine leg. They take three runs. A good chase from Usman Khawaja there.
Tossed up, full and on off, Abdullah Shafique gets forward and flicks it with the spin to mid-wicket.
Fuller and around off, this time batter presses forward and defends it back.
Turn and bounce, from around middle, Abdullah Shafique gets back and plays it down to leg gully.
Hurls across a length ball outside off, going straight on at 139 clicks, Imam-ul-Haq covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Uses the angle of the bowler and defends a length ball on the leg side.

FOUR! That's the first boundary from the bat of Imam-ul-Haq. Not in control though. Pat Cummins speeds in from 'round the wicket, lands it full and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq slices his attempted drive, past the diving Lyon at point, for a boundary.
This one is nice and straight, Abdullah Shafique works it off his pads to mid-wicket and picks up a single.
Too full and on middle, at 143.8 kph, Abdullah Shafique leans across, perhaps to flick but fails to close the face of his bat in time. It ends up rolling down straight towards mid on.
Shortish and on off, Abdullah Shafique plays it down from the back foot to backward point.
Floats it up on middle, kept out.
On the stumps, blocked.
Imam steps out again but this time it is spotted by Lyon who drags his length back. Imam looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. Half an appeal but turned down.
Steps out, gets a little too close to the pitch of the ball and pushes it back to the bowler.
Gives it air again and bowls it on the stumps, kept out.
Tosses it up on middle, defended.
There is a banner in the crowd saying - 'Usman Khawaja, apna hi ghar samjho!' Meaning - Usman Khawaja, feel at home. That's good to see.
A touch short and close to off, Abdullah Shafique opens the face of his bat late and guides it past point for a couple of runs.
This one is angling in from a length around off, at 135.9 kph, Abdullah Shafique brings down his bat at an angle and defends it to mid-wicket.
On a length and outside off, Abdullah Shafique presses forward and defends it gently to covers. He looks for a run but Imam-ul-Haq ain't interested.
Bouncer around off, Abdullah Shafique doesn't want to get adventurous against pace and ducks.
Full and around off, gently pushed in the gap at covers for a single.
Back of a length, around off and angling in, Imam blocks it in front of short leg.

TWO MORE! Byes this time! That has just about hit the off pole. It lands outside off and skids back in. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but does so inside the line. It goes past the outside edge, past the off pole and Carey fails to collect it. Two taken as it rolls towards fine leg. A productive over then for Pakistan and they are off to a decent start.

Was that a chance? A tough, very tough one actually! This is on middle, Abdullah Shafique looks to flick but it goes off the inner half quickly to the right of leg slip. He is late to react, it goes off his boot down towards fine leg for two.

SIX! Over the fence for the first biggie! That came out of nowhere. Abdullah Shafique was probably bored of blocking. Steps out, gets to the pitch of it and with the turn hits it right off the middle. There is a man back at long on but it sails over him and over the fence. Seen that a lot from Shafique in the recently concluded PSL.
A little too full, Abdullah Shafique uses his reach and works it to mid on.
Off the pad! Sharp turn though for Lyon! It lands outside off and spins back in. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but misses. It hits the pad and lobs on the leg side.
Loopy ball on off, defended.
A harmless nut to end! Outside off, left alone.
Changes the length and bangs it short. Imam-ul-Haq lets it go over him.
On middle, Imam-ul-Haq gets right behind the line and defends.
Two more! Good shot! Fuller and on off, Imam pushes it through covers for a couple.
Angled into the pads, Shafique works it through square leg for one.

EDGY FOUR! That does not carry! Really do not expect a lot of balls to carry to slip on this wicket. Especially when Abdullah Shafique defends as he is playing with really soft hands. This is on a length and around off, it lands and holds its line. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend right under his eyes. It goes off the outside edge, lands just short of Warner at first slip. He puts in quite a lazy effort as he tries to stop it with one hand, fails to do so and it goes behind for a boundary.
Just the single from the over then! On off, Imam comes forward and keeps it out.
Flatter and on middle, Imam plays it back to the bowler.
Now nudges this through square leg, with the turn for one.
On middle, blocked.
Loopy delivery, it lands on off. Abdullah Shafique defends. He pushed at that one, ended up playing at it ahead of his body.
Tosses it up on off, Abdullah Shafique works it on the leg side with the turn.
Little bit of swing but after he goes past the bat. On a length and around off, at 132.5 kph, Imam-ul-Haq offers no shot.
A bouncer around middle and leg at 133.5 kph, Imam-ul-Haq picks it early and ducks watchfully.
Cummins goes fuller this time, around off at 135.4 clicks, Imam-ul-Haq leans across and defends it from the inside portion of his bat to mid on.
Back of a length, around middle at 128.7 kph, Imam-ul-Haq is on his toes in defense.
Tosses it up on off, gets it to turn back in a little. Abdullah Shafique works it on the leg side.
Right on the button, first ball. Around off, angling in from a fuller length, Abdullah Shafique gets forward and defends with gentle hands to covers.
Change! Pat Cummins comes on.
Imam misses out! Need to put the loose deliveries away when runs are hard to come by. Short and outside off, Imam cuts it hard but to covers.
Solid! This one does not turn a lot. It lands on off and goes on with the arm. Blocked.
That is a good sharp turn! Half an appeal too but turned down. This lands on off and spins away. Imam lunges to defend but is beaten.
Really good from Lyon! Once again gives it air and lands it on middle, Imam lunges and looks to defend, this too goes off the outer half as it turns away towards point.
Well bowled! Floats it up, lands it on off, gets it to hold its line. Imam looks to defend, it goes more off the outer half to point.
Straightaway gets a lot of turn, slow turn but turn. The length is shorter and around off, Imam goes back and chops it to covers.
Change! Well, well, it is not Cummins, it is Nathan Lyon who comes on to bowl now.

That is good from Starc! Another tidy over and the pressure continues to build! This starts on middle and comes back in a little. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards short leg.
Back of a length and on middle, defended.
Confusion but no harm done! This time Abdullah Shafique wants to drop and run as he pushes it towards cover. Imam-ul-Haq sends him back though.
Good length and on off, defended.

That is really good running in the end! Had to put the dive but gets in. Tap and run will be of great importance at the moment as the Australians are giving nothing away. Length and on off, Imam pushes it towards covers and takes off. Marnus Labuschagne gets to the ball and as he turns, he fires it at the bowler's end but misses. Could have been close had he hit.
Fuller and outside off, left alone. We thought there would be a short ball coming up with a short leg coming in. Starc does a double bluff. Goes full, looking to catch the batter off guard.
Solid! End of a maiden from Josh Hazlewood! Good length and on off, Abdullah Shafique defends it right under his eyes.

He did go after that though but luckily for him, there was no edge! Good carry yet again on this wicket for Josh Hazlewood! Really bent his back there. Short and wide outside off. Abdullah Shafique looks to cut, he hops as he tries to do so. The ball goes past the top edge.

Goes a little too straight this time, probably looking to shape it away a little. Abdullah Shafique nudges it on the leg side. Abdullah Shafique is playing with very soft hands, he is just looking to use the pace of the bowler at the moment. Hardly going after anything.
On a length and just outside off, left alone. Really good from Australia. Just giving nothing away at the moment and building the pressure.

That is a lovely delivery! Josh Hazlewood runs in and bowls it fuller, gets it to shape away late from just outside off. Abdullah Shafique was tempted in going after the tempter, he looks to drive away from the body but is beaten.
Good length and on off, defended.

NOT OUT! GOING OVER! Australia lose a review. Not sure why that was taken, it just never looked close. The length here is shortish and on middle, Imam shuffles across and looks to flick but misses to get hit above the flap. A huge shout but turned down. There is a mid-pitch conference between Carey, Cummins and Starc and in the end, Cummins takes the review. Replays show that it is going over. Alex Carey's gesture suggested that he was not entirely convinced about the angle. Of course, he can't judge the height standing behind the stumps and perhaps someone from point or square leg could have been in a better position to tell. Nathan Lyon, who fields at point, was there but he was away from the three individuals holding a conflab. Australia need to be very careful with their reviews, can't afford to lose them, especially on an unresponsive pitch like this.
Review time! Starc was pleading there as he was appealing for an LBW. Turned down but it is reviewed. Seems a little high. Maybe umpire's call.

A bumper, at 137 KPH. Well-directed. Imam evades it. Good change of length, got good carry there. Starc still has not hit full pace here. He probably is looking to hit the right lines and lengths rather than bowling very fast.
Gets it right this time, makes the batter play as this is bowled on off and on a length. Defended.
Hint of movement, this is just outside off, shapes away further. Left alone.
Seems like it was an effort delivery from Starc. He banged it short and bowls it outside off. Not a lot of bounce there as Imam leaves it. It passes by his chest. Seems quite a slow wicket.

A single on the very first ball! On the pads, this is nudged down to fine leg for one. Imam will now be facing Starc for the very first time in this game. On the pads, Abdullah Shafique plays it down to fine leg and gets to the other end.

That is a beauty! The change of angle almost works. This is the kind of delivery Broad bowls to Warner and gets him on most occasions. From around the wicket, Josh angles it into the off pole which means Imam has to play, he prods forward and looks to defend but the ball lands and straightens. It just about goes past the outside edge. A beauty of a nut to end the over. Tight stuff from Australia so far. They need to continue to be patient.
Josh Hazlewood changes to around the wicket, with no swing on offer, he changes the angle. Lands it on a length and on off, it is kept out.
Just uses the pace of the bowler, stays back, opens the face and guides this past point for one.
Solid! Back of a length and on off, Abdullah Shafique stands tall and guides it to point.

A single to fine leg! Josh Hazlewood is probably looking to hit the front pad of Imam who does fall over quite often. This time though the line is way too straight, Imam clips it down to fine leg and turns the strike over to Abdullah Shafique who will be facing Josh Hazlewood for the first time today.
Good length and on off, angling away. Imam looks to defend, this goes more off the outer half. The fielder at point, runs to his right, dives and saves at least one.
A dot to end! Length and outside off, left alone. Both the batters have seemed quite comfortable in the 18 balls bowled so far.

Nicely played! Slightly shorter in length this time and a little bit of width on offer. Shafique stays back, uses the pace of the bowler and guides it past the diving point fielder. The gully fielder hares after it and keeps it down to two.

That is perfect! When there is no swing, you have to make use of the angle and that is what Starc did here. He lands it on off, Abdullah Shafique has to play at it, this lands and then slants away. Shafique is beaten as he tries to defend.
Just a little wider than he would like to be. The length is good but the line is well wide outside off. Shafique would leave that all day.

Good stuff from Starc! He can be wayward at times when the ball isn't doing much but for now, he has really caught a good line and length. Back of a length and on off, Abdullah Shafique guides it to point.
Abdullah Shafique probably misses out there! He gets one on the pads, batters here feed on such deliveries, he clips it but straight to square leg.

A dot to end a tidy first one from Josh Hazlewood too! He gets this one to come back in, this starts from around off, Imam tucks it to square leg. Josh Hazlewood did get some movement, unlike Starc but not a lot of it.
Extra bounce! Well played though by Imam! Back of a length and on off, this one gets big on the batter. Imam plays it with soft hands and it goes to the man at gully, on the bounce.

Two and Imam is underway too. A hint of movement in the air, for the first time in the 10 balls we have seen so far. The line though is a little too straight, it starts on middle and then swings back in. Imam works it through square leg and takes two.
Lands it on middle this time, the length is the same. Josh Hazlewood negotiates it well.
And again, bangs it on a length and around off, Imam is solid as he plays it to mid off.

Right on the money! This is exactly what you will get from Josh Hazlewood. He will keep hitting that good length and make you play on most occasions. This too is on a length and around off, looking to angle it away. Imam blocks it.
Josh Hazlewood to bowl from the other end then. Will he get some movement going?
A tempter to end! Wide outside off, slightly fuller. Abdullah Shafique is happy to let it go. Just the boundary from the first over then. Tidy from Starc.
Good stuff from Starc! Another one on a length and just outside off, Shafique covers his off pole and shoulders arms to it.
That is exactly what he does, drags his length back, bowls it just ahead of a good length and on off, Shafique gets right behind the line and keeps it out.

FOUR! Abdullah Shafique is off the mark with a boundary! Starc, in his search for swing, is put away. He goes full yet again, this one does not come back in too. Ends up being a half volley outside off. Abdullah Shafique opens the face of the bat and guides it past gully and into the fence. We will probably see Starc drag his length back now as there seems to be no swing on offer.
Yet another very full delivery from Starc, it is on off, no swing once again, Abdullah Shafique drives it back to the bowler.
Starc goes full, like he usually does in his first over, looking for some movement back into the right-hander. Nothing there. Abdullah Shafique lunges and strokes it to mid off.

The national anthems are being played in the stadium. First, it's Australia's, followed by Pakistan's. Now, we are done with all the formalities. The Australian team is spreading on the field now. Imam-ul-Haq and Abdullah Shafique are the openers for Pakistan. Clear blue skies at the moment, with the sun coming down hard. If they survive the initial period, it should be an excellent deck for batting. Mitchell Starc to steam in. Three slips and a gully in place. Here we go...
All the players from both sides are in the middle observing a minute silence in the memory of Rod Marsh.

So, Australia have gone with the tried and tested XI, and not included an extra spinner for a seamer. The presence of Cameron Green is offering them great balance. For Pakistan, playing XI is quite predicted but one would have expected Shan Masood to get the nod after a stellar PSL season. Their opening pair is slightly the weaker point but from number 3 to number 6, they have some extraordinary batters who will form the core of the batting. Iftikhar Ahmed at 7 looks like a defensive option, maybe they could have picked an extra bowler in place of him.
Australia (Playing XI) - David Warner, Usman Khawaja, Marnus Labuschagne, Steven Smith, Travis Head, Cameron Green, Alex Carey (WK), Pat Cummins (C), Mitchell Starc, Nathan Lyon, Josh Hazlewood.
Pakistan (Playing XI) - Imam-ul-Haq, Abdullah Shafique, Azhar Ali, Babar Azam (C), Fawad Alam, Mohammad Rizwan (WK), Iftikhar Ahmed, Nauman Ali, Sajid Khan, Naseem Shah, Shaheen Afridi.
Toss - Babar Azam gets the coin to fall in his favour and PAKISTAN ELECT TO BAT!

Some very sad news coming our way! Legendary Australian wicketkeeper, Rod Marsh, has passed away at 74 after suffering a heart attack. An absolute icon of the game and it's a great loss for everyone. We offer the family our deepest and most sincere condolences and may the soul of Rod Marsh rest in peace.

While we wait for the toss and updates related to both XIs, here's one trivia for you all! Did you know? The last time Australia played a Test match in Pakistan, Shaheen Afridi and Cameron Green were not even born.

It's going to be a big moment for Usman Khawaja. Born in this country, he has fond memories of his childhood. Khawaja shared on social media, one old picture of himself playing cricket as a kid, with an emotional message - 'Taken over 30 years ago, two weeks before we left for Australia. Me playing a shot on the old Rawalpindi ground (practice wickets). Who would have thought that I'd be back here for the green and gold. Can't wait to get back out there!' Go well, Uzzie!

We've already talked about Australia returning to Pakistan to play Test cricket for the first time since 1998. It's been a long wait and both teams will be up for this challenge. The Aussies may be slightly underprepared for this game as they arrived only at the start of the week and rain also wiped out their last training session on Thursday. That said, surely it cannot be an excuse in today's world. Pakistan, too, are looking a bit unsettled with their team composition for this format and only the conditions will determine where they stand with their planning. There's an air of unpredictability with both sides and that in a way is making things more compelling.

Test cricket in Pakistan! It's finally happening after a lot of planning by both the boards. After the disappointment of New Zealand leaving and England cancelling their tour, their arch-rivals Australia have fulfilled the promise of playing in this part of the world. The coming days are going to be exciting for the cricket starved crowd of Pakistan and we hope to witness Test cricket of the highest order. On that note, we welcome you for our coverage of this Test series, the first of which is in Rawalpindi. Just sit back and enjoy all the updates.
... MATCH DAY ...
We are back for the third innings. The players stride out to the middle. Abdullah Shafique and Imam-ul-Haq are at the crease.
... Third Innings ...

Now, it will be interesting to see Pakistan’s approach with the bat. Will they try and score quickly, get a lead of around 200 and declare, or will they be happy with a draw? Australia on the other hand, will hope to get wickets quickly, one or two in the first few overs and Pakistan could well succumb under pressure. The first 10 overs or so is quite key. Stay tuned.

For Pakistan, yes, it was Nauman Ali who got the six-fer but Shaheen Afridi bowled the best. He was unlucky but he was absolutely brilliant. Whenever he came on, he seemed like picking up a wicket. Naseem Shah on the other hand, was a bit off-color. The youngster bowled well in patches. In the end though, Pakistan have recovered well and Babar Azam will be happy as they did not concede a lead.

It was the top 4 for the Aussies who shone with the bat. Smith, Warner, Labuschagne and Khawaja. All crossed fifties but none of them managed to get to the three-figure mark. Green too contributed but fell after getting off to a decent start. The rest, however, failed to cash in on this very good batting wicket and had they done so, Australia could have scored over 500.

Pakistan have wasted no time this morning and have got a slender lead of 17 runs. It is the perfect start to Day 5 for them. The Aussies on the other hand, will be a tad disappointed to have fallen below the Pakistan score. From 407 for 4, they have been bundled out for 459. Although, they have done well to get close to Pakistan’s total.

OUT! LBW! Nauman Ali picks his sixth wicket and that is it for Australia! Nauman Ali serves a flatter ball, on off that goes on with the arm. Nathan Lyon kneels and looks to sweep but he misses and gets pinged on his pad. Ali appeals and the umpire raises his finger. Lyon though takes a review but to no avail. The Ball Tracker indicates three reds and it is plumb. Lyon, however, had already taken the walk back to the pavilion. Australia are bowled out for 459.
Josh Hazlewood is the last batter in.

OUT! LBW! That looked plumb in front! Shaheen Afridi doing what he does best! He runs in and serves a yorker, angling in from off. Mitchell Starc fails to dig it out and gets hit low on his pad. Shaheen Afridi appeals and the umpire agrees. Starc opts for a review straightaway! No bat involved, confirms the UltraEdge. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it indicates three reds. Pakistan have their ninth wicket.
Another ball, full and on middle. Lyon flicks but this time Nauman Ali at mid on dives to his right and half-stops it. Just the single.
A full ball, angling in from middle. Lyon prods and flicks it past the mid on fielder to take a couple of runs.
A length ball, angling in from middle. Nathan Lyon misses his flick shot and gets hit high on his pad.
A short ball, around leg. Mitchell Starc miscues his pull towards square leg and takes a single.
A full ball, outside off. Mitchell Starc digs it out back to the bowler.
Fuller and on off. Lyon gets forward and keeps it out. A wicket-maiden from Nauman Ali. Superb bowling!
BEATEN! This is tossed up, outside off. The ball spins past Lyon's outside edge as he tries to defend it off the front foot.
Tossed up, around off. Lyon blocks it off the front foot.
Nathan Lyon walks out to bat.

OUT! CAUGHT! A soft dismissal and Nauman Ali bags a five-wicket haul! He tosses it up nicely, outside off, enticing the batter to drive. Cummins prods and looks to drive it away from his body through cover. It goes off the outer half of the blade and he just chips it in the end towards Imam-ul-Haq at extra cover who takes a sharp catch. Pat Cummins stands there in disbelief. Pakistan strike early on Day 5!
Looped up, on a length, around off. Pat Cummins defends it off the front foot.
Tosses it up, around off. Pat Cummins gets forward to block it.
Nauman Ali to bowl from the other end.

Leg bye! Afridi comes 'round the wicket and serves a full ball, around leg. Pat Cummins misses his nudge on the leg side and the ball brushes off his pad before going to the keeper. Rizwan half-stops it with a dive and the batters take a leg bye.
FOUR! Nicely played! 450 comes up for Australia! A full ball, on middle. Cummins stays back, opens the bat face and steers it past the backward point fielder to bag a boundary.
Leg bye! A full ball, angling in from middle. Starc looks to flick but he misses and gets hit low on his pad. The ball rolls to the leg side for a leg bye.
A length ball, angling down leg. Mitchell Starc fails to get any bat on it as he tries to flick it.
Back of a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc leaves it alone.

Some movement straightaway for Shaheen! A length ball, nipping back in from middle. Mitchell Starc stays back to block but he misses and gets rapped on his pad. Shaheen appeals but the umpire, Aleem Dar is unmoved.

We are set for Day 5 of the first Test to get underway! The players of Pakistan stride out to the middle. Pat Cummins and Mitchell Starc are at the crease. Shaheen Afridi will start proceedings with the ball. Two slips and a gully in place. Here we go...

As far as game number 6 of the Women's World Cup is concerned, Pakistan Women have set a target of 191 runs for Australia Women. Will the Aussies make it two wins in a row and stay unbeaten in the tournament?

Australia will probably hope to do what India did to England in the last series between the two. The Indians managed to bowl the hosts out within two sessions after scoring quick runs in the first. Australia are well and truly capable of it and you can’t rule them out from doing so. The wicket though there was different from the one here. The Aussies though will hope it starts playing loads of tricks today.

Hello and a warm welcome to the coverage of the final day of the first Test between Australia and Pakistan. We have at least 90 overs on Day 5 to sneak in a result. The weather should be great and we should have a full day’s play. However, the game has moved at a very slow pace and we need things to happen very, very quickly if we are to see a result. Australia trail by 27 runs in the first innings and they will probably look to add quick runs and take some sort of a lead. Pakistan on the other hand, their first target will be to get the three wickets quickly, probably before the deficit is wiped off. The first session is important and that will give us a fair idea of where the game is heading towards.
... Day 5, Session 1 ...

Now the question on everybody’s mind, is a result still possible? Well, it surely is. If Australia manage to score quickly in the first session and take some sort of a lead, say 50, Pakistan can surely succumb under pressure and be bowled out quickly. They are an unpredictable side and you can’t just rule anything out when they’re playing. We believe Day 5 is going to be a fascinating one. The first ball will be bowled at 10.15 am IST (4.45 am GMT). Do join us then and make sure you tune in early for the buildup. Goodbye for now!

The day though belongs to the Aussies, in spite of losing five wickets. Firstly, we were quite lucky to get in the amount of overs we did, especially after the forecast and the amount of water that was on the outfield in the morning. The rain and the wicket being under the covers just flattened the surface a lot more. Marnus Labuschagne, Steven Smith and Cameron Green cashed in but all three will be disappointed to have not made it big. However, they have taken Australia in a strong position and they will hope that the tail can add some runs quickly on Day 5 and they get a healthy lead. Pakistan on the other hand, will just want to wrap it up quickly and then concentrate on their batting.

Coming to what happened now! The Aussies counter-attacked right after the break. Both Cameron Green and Steven Smith went after the pacers and scored freely. However, Babar Azam made a really good decision to get his spinners on, and that paid dividends. Nauman Ali got rid of both, Green and Smith which saw the visitors go defensive. At one stage, it seemed like they would end up taking a lead on Day 4 itself but are still 27 runs behind.

Have to say, it will be Pakistan who will be the happier of the two sides with the last session. They got three wickets and we assume, the Aussies had come out with a plan which wasn’t fulfilled. Saying that though, it is the visitors who are still ahead in this game, by just but still. If there is one side that can win this Test from here, it is them. However, a draw seems the most likely result heading into Day 5!
The umpires are checking the light again! The light meter suggests that it is too dark and the conditions aren't good enough for play to go on. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 4!
Tossed up, around off. Pat Cummins keeps it out.

Around off, blocked out.

The light meter is out! The umpires are checking whether the light is good enough for the play to be carried on. It looks fine and it is Babar Azam who brings himself into the attack now.
Short of a length, around off. Cummins blocks it out.

OUT! TIMBER! Naseem Shah strikes and this is a peach of a delivery by the youngster to get rid of Carey! Shah comes 'round the wicket and serves a length ball, just outside off. The ball nips back in slightly and Carey plays it down the wrong line as he tries to block it. The ball hits the top of off stump and Carey is a goner. Pakistan on top at the moment as Australia lose their seventh wicket now. Pat Cummins walks out to bat.
This is full and outside off. Alex Carey drives it wide of the mid off fielder and takes a couple of runs.

Bye! A full ball, angling down leg. Starc misses his nudge on the leg side and Rizwan behind the sticks half-stops it. The batters take a bye. Rizwan seems to have hurt his right hand yet again and looks in pain.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Mitchell Starc keeps it out.
FOUR! EDGY! Banged into the deck, around off. Starc stays back to defend but it goes off the outside edge past the first slip fielder and races away to the fence.

Back of a length, nipping down leg. Mitchell Starc hops in his crease to flick but fails to get any bat on it.
Bye! A full ball, angling down leg. Alex Carey misses his flick and Rizwan fails to grab it cleanly. The ball rolls away towards fine leg and they take a bye.

Good-length ball, around middle. Mitchell Starc nudges it around the corner and takes a single.
A full ball, angling down leg. Mitchell Starc misses his flick and Mohammad Rizwan does well behind the sticks to dive to his right to stop the ball.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Digs it short again and on the body, once again it comes at an uncomfortable height for Starc. He manages to nudge it down to fine leg for one.
Short and on the body, Starc fends it away on the leg side.
Good length and on off, this is pushed to covers.
Angling into the middle pole, Starc works it to mid on.
Fuller and outside off, left alone.
On a length, around middle. Carey blocks it off the front foot.
Floated, on a length, around off. Alex Carey lunges forward and keeps it out.
Tossed up, outside off. Alex Carey leans and pushes it towards mid off.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Carey punches it towards cover.
Tossed up, around off. Alex Carey gets forward to block it.
Flatter ball, on a length, around off. Alex Carey stays back and works it towards point.
A pinpoint yorker, around off. Mitchell Starc digs it out back to the bowler.
A well-directed bumper, around off. Starc stays back and looks to block but he gets hit high on his bat.
Another full ball, angling in from middle. Mitchell Starc jams it out watchfully.
On a length, around middle. Mitchell Starc nudges it through mid-wicket and takes a couple of runs.
Back of a length, down leg. Mitchell Starc leaves it alone.
Review! Babar Azam opts for a review as Mitchell Starc has been struck on his pad. Looked like going down leg to the naked eye.

NOT OUT! This was a yorker, around leg. Mitchell Starc fails to dig it out and gets hit low on his pad. Shaheen Afridi sppeals but the umpire says no. Babar Azam opts for a review and the Ball Tracker shows that the ball would have gone down leg. Starc survives.
Shaheen Afridi (25-5-76-1) is back into the attack.
A yorker-length ball, on middle. Alex Carey digs it out watchfully.
Tossed up, on middle. Alex Carey gets forward and defends.
Tossed up, on off. Alex Carey keeps it out.

FOUR! Excellent timing and even better from placement from Carey! A half-volley, outside off. Carey gets to the pitch of delivery and carves it past Shaheen Afridi at mid off to fetch himself a boundary. Lovely shot!
Flatter and quicker, on off. Alex Carey rocks back and punches it to mid off.
Flighted ball, around off. Carey blocks it solidly.
A wayward delivery, down leg. Mitchell Starc stays back and leaves it alone.

A full ball, outside off. Mitchell Starc prods and drives it to cover. Not in the gap though!
Floated, on a length, around off. Starc lunges forward and keeps it out.
Fuller and wider, outside off. Mitchell Starc pushes it back to the bowler.
Looped up, full and outside off. Carey gets down on his knee and sweeps it to deep square leg for one run.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Mitchell Starc dabs it onto the deck.
Floated, on a length, around off. Starc looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards the first slip fielder, on the bounce.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Mitchell Starc rocks back and punches it to the man at cover-point.
Slower through the air, on a length, around middle. Mitchell Starc gets forward and blocks it.
An overpitched ball, on middle. Starc digs it out.
Tossed up, on middle. Mitchell Starc stays back and pushes it towards mid on.
This is darted on the pads. Starc flicks it through square leg and collects a run.
Tossed up, outside off. Mitchell Starc gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller and wider, outside off. Starc prods and defends it.
Floated, around middle. Mitchell Starc keeps it out.
Carey plays another reverse sweep towards deep point and rotates the strike.
Flatter ball, on a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc pushes it through covers and takes a single to get off the mark.
On middle, Carey leans forward and defends. A maiden by Khan.
Slightly fuller and on off, this is pushed to covers.
Loopy ball on middle, blocked.
Tosses it up on middle, Carey keeps it out.
Fires it on middle again, Carey easily keeps it out.
Flatter and on off, defended.
Flatter and outside off, this stays low. Starc looks to push but it goes off the underedge and on the bounce to the first slip fielder.
Mitchell Starc walks out to bat.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! So the ploy to bowl from over the wicket and around Smith's pads has done wonders for Pakistan! Another Australian batter who gifts his wicket away! Nauman Ali serves a flatter ball, down leg. Smith prods and tries to sweep it fine through the fine leg region but he fails to do so. The ball brushes off his glove and goes to Mohammad Rizwan behind the sticks who takes a sharp catch. Pakistan are ecstatic as they should be! Another Aussie batter fails to go on and get a big one after getting set. Australia lose their sixth wicket now!
Commentary.Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Nauman Ali

Commentary.Commentary: Another ball, down leg. Steven Smith looks to whack it through fine leg but he misses.
Nauman serves a flighted ball, down leg. Steven Smith looks for a reverse sweep but he fails to get any bat on it.
Looped up, full and outside off. Alex Carey gets forward and reverse sweeps it to deep point. A single taken!
Floated, full and on middle. Alex Carey digs it out to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Top shot! Khan serves a flighted delivery, well outside off. Smith reaches out and carves it past the mid off fielder to bag a boundary.
Slower through the air, on a length, around off. Smith gets forward to block it.
Darted on the pads. Steven Smith prods and works it to square leg.
Floated, around middle. Smith keeps it out.
A loopy ball, on middle. Smith tucks it to the leg side.
Flatter and on off. Blocked out.

DRINKS! Australia now trail by 59 runs and there is still some time left in the day’s play. They would surely be eyeing a lead today. Pakistan on the other hand, probably have gone a little defensive. However, it is wickets which will stop the Aussies from scoring freely and one more breakthrough will see them bring the bowling all-rounders at the crease. An interesting passage awaits.

FOUR! Just over the slip fielder! Another ball, tossed up, outside off. Alex Carey gets down on his knee to reverse sweep yet again. He does not middle it this time as it goes off the top edge. Babar Azam at first slip hops to grab the ball but it goes over him and into the fence for another boundary.
FOUR! Nails his reverse sweep this time! Tossed up, outside off. Alex Carey kneels and reverse sweeps it behind square on the off side for a boundary.
Tossed up, around off. Alex Carey gets forward and blocks it.
Floated, full and on off. Alex Carey prods and just paddles it towards short fine leg. Not in the gap though!
A full ball, on middle. Steven Smith flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
TURN AND BOUNCE! A flatter ball, on leg and spinning away from the batter. Smith looks to defend off the back foot but he misses and gets hit high on his body.
A bit quicker, on a length, around middle. Alex Carey keeps it out.
Slower through the air, on middle, Carey blocks if off the front foot.

Flatter and on middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! A wicket against the run of play! Green has just thrown away his wicket as he could have hit this loose ball anywhere on the leg side. He would be gutted as he has also fallen just two runs short of his fifty. Nauman Ali serves a half-tracker, down leg. Green gets low and looks to whack it behind square on the leg side. He only manages to get a top edge which lobs up in the air towards the short fine leg fielder who was kept too fine intentionally. Iftikhar Ahmed there, makes no mistake and this is a much-needed breakthrough for Pakistan!
Commentary.Howout: c Iftikhar Ahmed b Nauman Ali

FOUR! CRUNCHED! Slightly shorter in length, outside off. Green gets on top of the bounce and slaps it through cover for another boundary.
Around off, blocked out.

FOUR! Overcooked from Nauman Ali and Green pounces on it! A full ball, outside off. Green gets to the pitch of it and smacks it through the extra cover region. Shaheen Afridi at long off runs to his left, puts in a dive to stop the ball but he fails to do so.
A loopy ball, outside off. Smith runs down the track and drags it wide of mid on for another quick run.
Flatter ball, on a length, around middle. Cameron Green hangs back and eases it to mid on for a quick single.
Shaheen goes for a yorker but ends up serving a low full toss, on the pads. Green tucks it towards fine leg and retains the strike by collecting a single.

Edged but safe! A full ball, angling in from outside off. Smith looks to push it through the off side but it goes off the outside edge which lands in front of the first slip fielder. Abdullah Shafique there, fumbles and the batters take a run.
A yorker-length ball, on off. Steven Smith digs it out back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Steven Smith stays back and defends it towards mid on.
Short of a length, around leg. Cameron Green swivels and tucks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Shaheen serves a full ball, around off. Cameron Green gets forward to defend.
Looped up, on a length, around off. Steven Smith covers the line of the ball to block it.
Floated, around off. Steven Smith gets back and blocks it out.
Smith skips down early so Nauman serves it wider, outside off. Steven Smith gets to the pitch of the ball and defends it to the off side.
Flatter ball, on a length, outside off. Steven Smith hangs back and punches it to extra cover.
Fuller in length, outside off. Cameron Green skips down and works it to long off. The batters cross ends.
Tosses it up, around off. Cameron Green keeps it out off the front foot.
A full ball, around off. Steven Smith stays back and eases it to mid off.
Shaheen persists with full-length stuff, outside off. Steven Smith sits back and pushes it towards mid off.
Another ball, full and outside off. Steven Smith drives it to the fielder at extra cover. No run there!
Pitches it up, around off. Smith defends it off the front foot.
Good-length delivery, around off. Steven Smith hangs back to block it.
Full and outside off. Steven Smith drives but straight to the cover fielder.

We are back for the final session of Day 4! The players have made their way out to the middle. Steven Smith and Cameron Green are at the crease. It is Shaheen Afridi who will start proceedings with the ball for Pakistan.
... Day 4, Session 3 ...

Pakistan were quite disciplined with the ball! There was absolutely nothing on offer, neither for the spinners, nor for the pacers. The second new ball did do a bit, the ball zipped a lot more off the surface and there was some movement earlier on. The hosts did manage to strike twice, one taken by Shaheen Afridi and the other by Nauman Ali but more or less, the Aussie batters have looked at ease. All the hosts can do is be patient and just not give away easy runs to the visitors. The Aussies are still 112 runs behind, so it is about being patient and optimistic for the home side. Can the last session go their way? The last session begins at 4.05 pm IST (10.35 am GMT). Do join us then.

The game continues to move along at a slow pace! Two wickets in this one and things might have looked different at one stage but this Smith-Green stand has taken Australia to shafer shores and have taken them to a position from where Australia SHOULD not lose this game. Both Marnus Labuschagne and Steven Smith started off from where they left off on Day 3. The two added over 100 before Marnus Labuschagne fell 10 short of his ton. Head did not last for long in the middle and a collapse seemed on the cards but Smith has held fort at one end and Green has looked solid since the time he has come out. Bat, bat and keep batting is what the message will be for the two.
Fuller in length, on off. Cameron Green gets forward and drives it to the man at extra cover. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 4!
Slower through the air, fuller and on off. Green defends it off the front foot.
Floated, on a length, around off. Green covers the line and gets solid in his defence.
Ali bowls it slower through the air, full and on off. Cameron Green gets forward and keeps it out.
A quicker ball, around off. Cameron Green gets behind the line and defends it.
Slightly short and outside off. Green stays back and punches it towards extra cover.
On a length, around middle. Green gets deep in his crease and eases it to long on for a run.
A quicker ball, going on with the arm from middle. Cameron Green rocks back and dabs it onto the deck watchfully.
Floated, full and outside off. Green prods and pushes it towards mid off.
A length ball, drifting onto the pads. Smith tucks it around the corner for a single.
This is a flatter ball, on middle. Smith keeps it out with ease.
A loopy ball, on middle. Steven Smith defends off the front foot.
BEATEN! TURN AND BOUNCE! Ali tosses it up nicely, just outside off. Cameron Green looks to block off the back foot but the ball spins past his outside edge. Terrific delivery to end the over.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Cameron Green covers the line and keeps it out.
Tosses it up, outside off. Steven Smith drives it down to long off for a single.
This is bowled well wide, outside off. Steven Smith does not bother playing at that one.
Tosses it up, around off. Steven Smith gets forward and defends it.
Flatter ball, outside off. Steven Smith leaves it alone.
A loopy ball, on a length, on off. Cameron Green skips down the track, smothers the spin and pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Cameron Green hangs back to block it.
Around off, blocked out.
Floated, full and outside off. Steven Smith looks for a booming drive but it goes off the inner half of the bat towards long off for a single.
This is darted on the pads. Steven Smith rocks back and turns it to square leg.
Fuller and on middle. Smith defends it back to the bowler.
A bit quicker through the air, on middle. Green stays back and dabs it onto the deck.
Floated, on a length, outside off. Cameron Green drives but finds the extra cover fielder yet again.
A loopy ball, outside off. Cameron Green leans and pushes it to cover.
Tossed up, outside off. Cameron Green lunges and drives it to the man at extra cover.
Floated, full and outside off. Cameron Green prods and pushes it towards extra cover.
Flatter ball, around off. Cameron Green hangs back and defends it.
Khan serves a flighted delivery, on a length, around off. Steven Smith lunges forward and defends it.
A tad short, on middle. Green punches it down to long on for a run.
A bit quicker through the air, on middle. Steven Smith stays back and works it to deep square leg for a single.
Flatter and quicker, on middle. Smith tucks it towards square leg but not in the gap.
This is around middle and leg. Smith wrists it towards square leg.
Tosses it up, around off. Steven Smith gets forward and defends it.
Floated, full and outside off. Cameron Green leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
FOUR! Punished by Green! A length ball, drifting onto the pads. Green rocks back and whips it through the mid-wicket region. The ball races away to the fence.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Cameron Green keeps it out.
Around off, blocked out.
Fuller and outside off. Smith pushes it towards long off and rotates the strike.

FOUR! Excellent use of the feet and Smith pierces the gap to perfection! Tosses it up, just outside off. Smith advances down the track and caresses it through the extra cover region to bag a boundary.
A loopy ball, outside off. Green skips down the track and yorks himself in the process. He digs it out back to the bowler.
A bit quicker, on a length, around off. Cameron Green keeps it out off the back foot.
Floated, full and on middle. Cameron Green gets forward and eases it to mid on.
Tossed up, around middle. Cameron Green keeps it out.
Floated, full and on middle. Cameron Green prods and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball, on middle. Cameron Green stays back to block it onto the deck.
Tosses it up, around off. Smith blocks it solidly off the front foot.
Another loopy ball, full and just outside off. Smith gets to the pitch of the ball and keeps it out.
Slower through the air, around off. Steven Smith gets forward and defends it.
Flatter ball, on off. Steven Smith blocks it out.
Nicely done! Floated, on a length, outside off. Green waits for the ball to turn and then guides it through the third man region. Fawad Alam cuts it off and the batters take three runs.
Tossed up, around off. Green prods and pushes it towards cover.
On off, defended.
That is nicely played in the end! Outside off, Smith waits and then guides it past point for two.
Length again and on off, Smith comes forward and keeps it out.
Angled into the pads, Smith works it to mid-wicket.
Shot! Just a push! Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for three.
On a length and around off, defended.
Well bowled! The arm ball to end, Smith looks to defend, it goes off the inner half on the leg side.
Tosses it up on middle, Steven Smith lunges and keeps it out.
Flatter and on off, Smith defends.
Tossed up on off, Smith pushes it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, blocked.
Tossed up on middle, defended.

Fifty for Smith! Another superb knock from one of the best in the world! He though has not been converting his fifties into big scores lately but has a chance here. Can he do so? There are three batters before him who have got to fifty but haven't converted it into a ton. He gets there with a controlled pull through square leg for one.
A single now as this is worked through mid-wicekt.
A bumper, Green ducks under it.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Good length and on off, Smith pushes it to covers.
Angled into middle, this is worked towards wide mid on for one.
Fuller and on off, Smith pushes it to mid off.
Slower through the air and lands it on middle, Smith plays it to covers.
Floats it up on off, Smith leans forward and keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, this is pushed to mid off.
On middle, defended.
FOUR BYES! Down the leg side, Smith looks to sweep but misses. It straightens and hence, goes past the keeper for a boundary in the fine leg region.

Review! Babar Azam opts for a review as Cameron Green is pinged on his pad. Was there any bat involved in it? Yes, the UltraEdge shows that there was a slight inside edge before the ball hit Green's pad. Pakistan lose a review.

NOT OUT! There is an inside edge! Either way it seemed the impact would be outside off. Not a good review to be honest and Pakistan lose one. It is a length ball around off, Green plants his front foot outside the line of off and tries to defend with bat close to the pad. It surely hits the front pad. A huge appeal but turned down. Pakistan review but Ultra Edge shows there is an inside edge.
Two! Angled into the pads, Green works it through mid-wicket and takes two.
Angled into middle, this is pushed to mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
Yet another one on a length and around off, Green plays it to mid on.
Good length and outside off, left alone.
Tossed up, around off. Cameron Green prods and pushes it towards mid off for a quick single.
A bit quicker this time, on middle. Cameron Green stays back and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery, around off. Green defends off the front foot.
Ali tosses it up nicely, around off and the ball spins away after landing. Cameron Green skips down the track and pushes it to the off side in the end.
This is a flatter ball, on a length, around off. Green goes deep in his crease and blocks it.
Floated, full and on middle. Steven Smith pushes it towards mid on and takes a single.
Good length and on middle, defended.
That is a good leave in the end! Length and around middle, moves away. Green leaves it alone. It goes just over the off pole. Left on length. Trusting the wicket.
Goes short now and on the body, Green ducks under it.
On middle, Green plays it on the leg side.
Attacks the stumps, on middle, defended.
Angled into the pads, Green looks to nudge it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads.
Another one tossed up on off, this is pushed down to long off for one.
Floats it up on middle, gets it to drift back in. Blocked.
On middle, Green comes forward and blocks.
Tosses it up on off, this is pushed down to long off for one.
Flatter and on middle, Smith defends.
On middle, defended.
Off the underedge! Crowd catch! Fuller and outside off, Green looks to drive but it goes off the underedge and on the bounce to the keeper.
Fuller and on off, Green pushes it to covers.
Down the leg side, Green leaves it alone.
Angled into the pads, this is nudged through square leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Smith pushes it to covers.
That has hurt Rizwan! Down the leg side, Steven Smith lets it go. The keeper dives to his left and looks to stop. It bounces just in front of him. Rizwan does well to stop it.
Slower and on off, it lands and turns away. Green looks to defend but it goes off the outer half to point.
Flatter and on middle, defended.

DRINKS! Pakistan have done well to get a couple of wickets and the second new ball certainly seems to be doing the trick for them. Australia will need to be careful here as they cannot afford to lose wickets in a cluster. Pakistan would look to keep chipping with wickets and make full use of the new ball. Cameron Green walks out to bat.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Two wickets in quick succession for Pakistan and the move to get Nauman Ali on has worked wonders. Just the two boundaries for Head. He just misread the length here. This is a delivery, he should have probably played on the front foot but goes back, tries the approach the Aussies have been using so far but since it is the new ball, it does not work. It is outside off, tossed up. Head goes back and looks to cut, this one skids through, it takes the outside edge and the keeper, Mohammad Rizwan does the rest. The Aussies still 150 runs behind.
Commentary.Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Nauman Ali

Commentary.Commentary: A single now as this is pushed through covers.
On middle, defended.
Flatter and on middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Nauman Ali (19-4-59-1) is back into the attack.

FOUR! Cut away! Short and wide outside off, Head cuts it through point and this one races away to the fence. Lovely shot. Very stylish. He stayed so low while cutting that. Two boundaries in the over then.
FOUR! Clipped away! Full and on the pads, Head clips it through wide mid on. The fielder runs to his left and dives but fails to stop it. A boundary to get off the mark.
Probably tried to get it back in from outside off. This goes on with the arm though. Left alone.
Again, relentless stuff! Length and on off, Head blocks it towards cover.

Now angles it on middle, Head plays it to mid on. Not easy times for Head. The two pacers are bowling with fire, hitting the right lines and lengths and asking questions on every delivery. Can he weather the storm?
Outside off, on a length, this one stays low a touch. Left alone.

Edged but safe! Another ball, on a length, just outside off. Steven Smith stays back to defend but it goes off the outside edge and falls just short of the first slip fielder. Lovely bowling from the youngster!
A length ball, way outside off. Steven Smith lets it through to the keeper.
Short of a length, around off. Steven Smith keeps it out.
FOUR! EDGY! Back of a length, around off. Steven Smith hangs back to block but it takes the outside edge and races away through the keeper and wide first slip for a boundary.
A length ball, around off. Smith shuffles across and clips it to the leg side for a couple of runs.
On a length, around off. Steven Smith blocks it off the back foot.
Travis Head walks out to bat.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Marnus Labuschagne just does not want to go. He stands there for a second in disbelief after the catch is taken. He had played so well and deserved a ton. His first game in Asian conditions for the Aussies in Tests, gets into the nervous 90s and falls. Second player in this game for the Aussies to fall in the 90s. The second new ball does the trick for Pakistan. Shaheen Afridi finally gets a wicket. He deserves it, he has been excellent so far and is rewarded. He goes around the wicket, lands it just behind a driving length. Draws Marnus Labuschagne ahead who looks to drive. The length was not quite there. The ball lands and moves away. Takes the outside edge and the fielder at first slip, Abdullah Shafique takes a superb catch diving to his right. That was going quickly to him. Marnus Labuschagne was probably eager to get to his ton quickly. Had it been earlier in the innings, he would have probably left that ball but this time went chasing after it.
Commentary.Howout: c Abdullah Shafique b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Clipped away and Marnus Labuschagne moves into the 90s! On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket and it races away to the fence.
Outside off, left alone.
Slightly fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to mid off.
Good length and on off, this is kept out.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length and on off, Smith defends.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
On middle, it is pushed to mid on.

EDGY FOUR! Unlucky but Marnus Labuschagne won't care! Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Marnus Labuschagne once again with a half stride forward looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge past second slip and to the third man fence.
Fuller and on off, Marnus Labuschagne pushes it to mid off.
Outside off, left alone.
