Floats it up on off, Imam defends.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Slower and outside off, left alone.
Outside off, not played at.
Good shot but for no runs! Length and on off, it is driven nicely but to covers.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Good length and on off, defended.

Edged but safe! Good fielding by Lyon again! Outside off, shaping away. Abdullah Shafique goes after it, it flies off the outside edge wide of the diving gully fielder. Lyon runs to his left from deep point, dives and saves two again for his side.
Well fielded! Outside off, this is guided through backward point. Lyon runs to his left, slides and makes a good stop.
Outside off, left alone.
Now takes one as he works it through square leg.
Well played in the end! Abdullah Shafique gets down the wicket, he does not get to the pitch of the ball but puts in a good stride forward and hits it against the turn through covers for two.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off again, kept out.
On off, blocked.
Length and on off, this one also shapes away. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend, it goes off the outer half through point for one.
Outside off, Imam opens the face of the bat and guides it down to third man for one.
Outside off, left alone.
On the stumps, Imam shows the full face of the bat and plays it to mid off.
Good length and on off, Imam shows the full face of the bat and plays it back to the bowler.
Some inward movement for Starc! It is on middle, Imam clips it to mid-wicket.
On off, blocked.
This lands outside off and turns back in. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but it goes off the inner half on the leg side.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Goes short again, this is also cut through point for one.
Shorter and outside off, Imam cuts it through point and takes two.
Tossed up, very full and on off, it is jammed out to covers.
Starc pitches it up, around off. Abdullah Shafique gets forward and blocks it solidly.
Back of a length, around middle. Abdullah Shafique covers the line and defends it to the on side.
Fuller in length, down leg. Imam-ul-Haq tickles it to fine leg and collects a single.
A full ball, angling in from middle. Imam-ul-Haq gets forward and pushes it to mid on.
Good-length delivery, around off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it off the back foot.
Starc starts with a full ball, on middle. Imam-ul-Haq prods and eases it to mid-wicket.
Tosses it up, around off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it off the front foot. A maiden over from Nathan Lyon!
Flatter and quicker, on middle. Abdullah Shafique nudges it to mid-wicket.
On a length, around middle and turning in late. Abdullah Shafique waits for the turn and then glances it to the man at short fine leg.
This is darted on the pads. Abdullah Shafique hangs back and tucks it to short fine leg.
Floated, full and outside off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it off the front foot.
Flatter ball, around middle and turning in late. Abdullah Shafique stays back and wrists it behind square on the leg side.

We are back for the second session of Day 5! The players stride out to the middle. Abdullah Shafique and Imam-ul-Haq to resume their innings. Nathan Lyon will start with the ball after the Lunch break.
... Day 5, Session 2 ...

Right then! With 69 overs still remaining in the day, it will be interesting to see the approach of both sides in the second session. The second session will give us a fair idea about where this Test match is heading. Do join us for an exciting session which begins at 1.10 pm IST (7.40 am GMT).

Earlier, Pakistan managed to pick the remaining three wickets quickly and they made sure that the Aussie tail doesn't wag much. Shaheen Afridi and Nauman Ali were brilliant for the hosts and then it was onto their batters to score quickly. Imam-ul-Haq and Abdullah Shafique didn't disappoint them as they scored at a decent rate and have managed to go into Lunch unscathed. The pair has stitched together an unbeaten stand of 76 runs and Pakistan will hope that they go big once the play resumes after Lunch, if they are to push hard for a result here. Although, a result looks unlikely at the moment.

A session that has well and truly gone Pakistan's way! They have ticked all the boxes so far on Day 5 and we feel that they'll go hard post the Lunch break, with all their wickets intact. The pitch still hasn't deteriorated that much and it is going to be hard work for the Aussie bowlers.
Marnus Labuschagne continues to toss it up, lands it on off, it is worked to mid on. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 5!
FOUR! That is a lovely shot! Uses his feet and makes it into a full toss, it is driven through covers for a boundary.
Slightly shorter again, Abdullah Shafique pulls it through mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
A single as this is worked through mid-wicket.
On off, this is pushed to mid on.
On the stumps Imam defends it out.
Yet another tidy over! On the stumps, blocked.
Flatter and on off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it to mid on.
On off, this stays a touch low. Abdullah Shafique defends.
On the stumps, kept out.
On middle, blocked.
This lands outside off and turns back in, it is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, defended.
Fuller and outside off, Imam pushes it to covers.
Gives it air and lands it on off, it is flicked to mid-wicket.
On middle, this is worked to mid on for one.
Flighted and on off, defended.
A single to end as this is worked with the spin through square leg.
Outside off, shortish. Imam rocks back and cuts it through point for one.
Gives it air and lands it outside off, it is driven to covers.
Yet again this one is well outside off, Imam shoulders arms to this one.
Another one tossed up and bowled well outside off, not played at.
Outside off, left alone.
Floats it up on off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it to covers.
Shorter and outside off, Abdullah Shafique looks to cut but underedges it on the off side.
Shorter and on middle, Imam works it through square leg for one.
Fuller and on off, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Flighted and on off, Imam pushes it to covers.
Another loopy delivery on off, blocked.
Floats it up on off, Abdullah Shafique defends.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Another one tossed up on off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it to mid off.
On the stumps, defended.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Flatter and on middle, defended.
Angled into the pads, Imam works it to square leg.

Review! Pat Cummins has opted for a review for LBW! Was there any bat involved in it? The UltraEdge shows that there was no bat involved. The Ball Tracker indicates that the impact was outside off so the on-field decision remains.

NOT OUT! The impact is well outside off. Always seemed that way. Australia lose a review. This is given a nice loop. It lands on off. Abdullah Shafique looks to play the paddle sweep but the ball dips at the very end, sneaks under the bat and hits the pad. A huge shout but turned down. It is reviewed. Replays show that the on-field call is the right one.
Outside off, left alone.
Lands it well again, floats it up on off, this is pushed back to the bowler.
Skips down the track now and eases it down to long on for one.
Lands it well, on off, Imam works it to mid-wicket.
Time for some leg spin as Marnus Labuschagne comes into the attack now.

Lands it around off, Abdullah Shafique comes forward and blocks. A really good over from Nathan Lyon! Unlike the first innings, he is bowling it outside off and getting it to turn back in. That is where he becomes very dangerous, that turn and the bounce he gets is what causes the batters problems.
Nicely tosses it up and on off, Shafique works it to mid-wicket.
Another one floated up on off, defended.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, blocked.

FOUR! How has that missed the off pole? What a delivery! This lands outside off, well outside off and turns back in. Abdullah Shafique lunges and looks to defend, it takes the inside edge and just about kisses the off pole, it goes very close past it and down to the fine leg fence.
Goes short and on middle, this is pulled through square leg for one. Cracking shot just for one.
On off, defended.
Angled into the pads, Imam works it through square leg for one.
Good length now and on off, Imam hangs back and defends.
That is very well played! Short and on middle, Abdullah Shafique, with one leg up in the air, pulls it through mid-wicket for one. They should have ran better, there was a chance of two there.
Slight halt in play. Imam-ul-Haq has been struck on his forearm and he looks in pain. The physio is out with the magic spray. Imam-ul-Haq looks fine now and we are good to resume.

Just over! Leg bye signaled though so would not have mattered if it had gone to hand. Short and on the body, Imam looks to evade it, it hits him on the forearm, then the chest and goes over Carey and down to fine leg for a leg bye. He is in pain now.
Tosses it up nicely, well outside off. Abdullah Shafique stretches forward and blocks it.
Fuller and wider, outside off. Abdullah Shafique keeps it out.

Shouts of catch it but the ball falls short of Lyon! A bit short, outside off and spinning in late. Abdullah Shafique rocks back and chips it back to the bowler uppishly. The ball bounces just in front of Lyon who tries to grab it.
Floated, full and outside off. Abdullah Shafique gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq slaps it through cover and takes a single.
Tossed up, well outside off. Abdullah Shafique smothers the spin and eases it to long on for a run.
Back of a length, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq prods to defend but it takes the outside edge which rolls towards the gully fielder.
A full ball, around middle. Abdullah Shafique tries to defend but it goes off the thick inside edge towards fine leg for a run.
A short ball, angling in from outside off. Abdullah Shafique sways away from the line of the ball.
Back of a length, outside off. Abdullah Shafique gets on top of the bounce and dabs it onto the deck.
Fuller in length, around off. Abdullah Shafique keeps it out.
A full ball, around middle. Abdullah Shafique looks to flick and the ball takes the outside edge. Luckily for Abdullah Shafique, the ball falls short of the slip fielder.
Flatter and quicker, on a length, around off. Imam-ul-Haq keeps it out.
Tosses it up, outside off. Abdullah Shafique skips down the track, smothers the spin and eases it to long on for a single.
Around off, blocked out.
Floated, full and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq drives it down to long off for one run.
SIX! Nails his shot this time! Imam-ul-Haq advances down the track to this length ball and lofts it back over the bowler's head to fetch a maximum.
Tosses it up, on middle. Imam-ul-Haq skips down the track and pushes it to mid on.
BEATEN! A length ball, around the corridor of uncertainty. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but the ball zips past his outside edge. Lovely bowling from the Aussie skipper.
A short ball, around off. Abdullah Shafique stays back and dabs it onto the deck with soft hands.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. Imam-ul-Haq tucks it behind square on the leg side and takes a single.
Short of a length, nipping back into the batter. Imam-ul-Haq misses his nudge on the leg side.
This is angling down leg. Imam-ul-Haq misses his flick and the ball brushes off his pad before going to Alex Carey behind the sticks.
Good-length ball, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq keeps it out.

DRINKS! Pakistan have certainly come out with some intent and have started brilliantly. They are going at a brisk rate and Pakistan would hope the same can continue. Australia on the other hand, need to stem the run-flow and also pick up a wicket if possible. Can they do so? We will find out.
Another forward defensive stroke to this ball on off.
Floats it up on off, kept out.
Another one nicely flighted and on off, blocked.
Floats it up on middle, Abdullah Shafique leans forward and keeps it out.
FOUR! Pakistan are scoring quickly here! Short and wide outside off, Abdullah Shafique goes back and pushes it through covers and this one races away to the fence.
Tossed up on off, turning in. Defended.
A short ball, around leg. Imam-ul-Haq ducks underneath.
Edged but safe! A length ball, around off and angling across the left-hander. Imam-ul-Haq tries to block but it goes off outside edge and goes to the gully fielder, on the bounce.
A full ball, around leg. Abdullah Shafique tickles it to fine leg and takes a single this time.
On a length, around off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it out.
BEAUTY! Good-length ball, just outside off that shapes away a bit. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but the ball zips past his outside edge. Good comeback from the Aussie skipper.

NO BALL AND FOUR! Cummins errs in line again! Another ball, drifting onto the pads. Abdullah Shafique tickles it through fine leg and fetches another boundary. Pat Cummins oversteps and the umpire signals a no ball.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Cummins starts with a loosener, a length ball, around leg. Abdullah Shafique glances it through fine leg and collects a boundary.
Pat Cummins brings himself into the attack now. He replaces Mitchell Starc.
A bit quicker through the air from Lyon, around off. Imam-ul-Haq gets back in his crease to block it.
Tosses it up, on off. Imam-ul-Haq gets solid in his front foot defence.
This is darted on the pads. Imam-ul-Haq rocks back and nudges it towards square leg.
Floated, on middle. Abdullah Shafique tucks it to the leg side for a single.
Sharp turn! Tossed up, on a length, well outside off. Abdullah Shafique looks to play it across the line but he misses as the ball sneaks through his bat and pad.
Tosses it up, around off. Abdullah Shafique keeps it out.
Short of a length, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq hangs back to defend it.
Another short ball, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq ducks underneath.
FOUR! Nicely timed! A full ball, on middle. Imam-ul-Haq flicks it behind square on the leg side and bags another boundary.
On a length, down leg. Imam-ul-Haq lets it be.

FOUR! Aerial but Imam-ul-Haq is lucky to escape! This is a well-directed short ball, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq looks to pull but the ball hurries onto him and he mistimes it in the air wide of the deep square leg fielder. The ball falls just wide of Nathan Lyon at deep square leg who dives to his left. Two bounces and into the ropes.
Back of a length, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq stays back and blocks it out.
Tosses it up, around off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it off the front foot.
That stayed a bit low! A loopy ball, outside off and turning in late. Abdullah Shafique stays back to defend but the ball keeps a bit low and gets the toe end of his bat.
Floated, full and on off. Abdullah Shafique prods and defends it.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Tosses it up, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq skips down and pushes it to cover.

FOUR! EDGY! Turn straightaway for Lyon! This is a flatter ball, around off and spinning away from the left-hander. Imam-ul-Haq stays back to block but it goes off the outside edge past the first slip fielder and into the third man fence.
Nathan Lyon comes into the attack.
Starc goes full and outside off. Abdullah Shafique leans and drives it wide of deep cover for a couple of runs.
FOUR! CUT AWAY! Width on offer and Abdullah Shafique pounces on it. Short of a length, outside off. Abdullah Shafique slaps it past the point fielder and bags a boundary.
Another ball, short and around off. Abdullah Shafique keeps it out.
Back of a length, around off. Abdullah Shafique sits back in his crease and dabs it onto the deck.
A length ball, around middle and leg. Imam-ul-Haq tickles it to fine leg and hands the strike back to Abdullah Shafique.
Good-length ball, way down leg. Imam-ul-Haq does not bother playing at it.
A full ball, angling in from middle. Abdullah Shafique flicks but Nathan Lyon at mid-wicket, dives to his left and stops the ball.
Pitched up, around off. Abdullah Shafique gets forward and keeps it out.
Good-length ball, nipping back in from middle. Abdullah Shafique misses his nudge on the leg side and gets hit high on his pad.
A length ball, around leg. Imam-ul-Haq nudges it around the corner and takes a run.
On a length, around off. Imam-ul-Haq leans and keeps it out on the off side.
Good-length ball, around off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it off the front foot.
Slightly shorter in length, well outside off. Abdullah Shafique lets it through to the keeper.
Back of a length, outside off. Abdullah Shafique leaves it alone.

An overthrow and they get five runs! Good-length ball, around off. Imam-ul-Haq taps it towards cover and takes off for a single. Usman Khawaja runs in from cover and misses his shy at the bowler's end. There is no one backing up and the ball races away to the fence. Sloppy from Australia!
Starc goes full and outside off. Abdullah Shafique slices it towards deep point for one run. Both the openers are up and running now!
This is darted on the pads. Imam-ul-Haq tucks it towards deep square leg and takes a single.
Back of a length, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq stays back to block.
Pitches it up, just outside off. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards the slip fielder, along the ground.
Hazlewood serves a full ball, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq flicks it past the mid-wicket fielder and gets off the mark with a single.
Another ball, full and around middle. Imam-ul-Haq keeps it out.
Back of a length, just outside off. Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone.
Pitches it up, around off. Imam-ul-Haq gets forward and defends it.
On a length, around off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it off the front foot.
Josh Hazlewood to share the new ball.
Good-length ball, well outside off. Abdullah Shafique does not bother playing at that one.
Fuller in length, around middle. Abdullah Shafique gets forward and defends it awkwardly towards mid-wicket.
This is a length ball, around middle. Abdullah Shafique prods and keeps it out.
Full and outside off. Abdullah Shafique lets it through to the keeper.
On a length, outside off. Abdullah Shafique leaves it alone.
Back of a length, down leg. Abdullah Shafique tries to flick but he misses. A stifled appeal for caught behind but the umpire is unmoved.
